259
00:12:48.935 --> 00:12:52.230
"A rose by any other name..."

260
00:12:55.984 --> 00:12:57.069
(DANIEL LAUGHS)

261
00:12:57.152 --> 00:12:58.820
JACK: Guys. what's happening?

262
00:12:59.488 --> 00:13:00.489
Whoa.

263
00:13:01.073 --> 00:13:02.324
Look at that.

264
00:13:02.991 --> 00:13:03.992
Whoa.

265
00:13:09.331 --> 00:13:10.457
JACK: It's gas!

266
00:13:10.665 --> 00:13:12.751
MERRITT: Relax. Just dry ice.

267
00:13:13.543 --> 00:13:14.544
Cool.

268
00:13:15.504 --> 00:13:16.880
Wait. What do you think this is all about?

269
00:13:17.089 --> 00:13:18.590
Hang on. Hang on.

270
00:13:22.260 --> 00:13:23.428
(MOANS)

271
00:13:23.678 --> 00:13:24.805
I got nothin'.

272
00:13:25.013 --> 00:13:26.723
Okay. Thank you. Thank you for the delay.

273
00:13:26.932 --> 00:13:28.809
I'm just trying to create the space for wisdom.

274
00:13:29.017 --> 00:13:32.020
Okay. so you're like Buddha.
if he wasn't so enlightened.

275
00:13:32.104 --> 00:13:33.480
And you're like Jesus.

276
00:13:33.563 --> 00:13:36.108
if he was arrogant
and all of his miracles were fake.

277
00:13:36.191 --> 00:13:39.444
Okay. lovebirds. get a room.
Danny. be honest. Did you do this?

278
00:13:39.528 --> 00:13:40.654
No. Wait. did you?

279
00:13:40.737 --> 00:13:42.030
I wish.

280
00:13:42.531 --> 00:13:44.783
Why didn't anyone ask me if I did it?

281
00:13:45.784 --> 00:13:46.785
Oh. great.

282
00:13:52.416 --> 00:13:53.917
JACK: Electricity is out.

283
00:13:55.085 --> 00:13:56.586
Well. let's check.

284
00:14:00.841 --> 00:14:01.883
Whoa.

285
00:14:10.434 --> 00:14:12.018
(HENLEY LAUGHS)

286
00:14:13.603 --> 00:14:15.105
HENLEY: Blueprints.

287
00:14:15.939 --> 00:14:17.274
DANIEL: They're incredible.

288
00:14:18.733 --> 00:14:20.110
JACK: Who do you think did this?

289
00:14:20.193 --> 00:14:22.362
I don't know. but I really want to meet them.

290
00:14:24.364 --> 00:14:25.949
It's a show.

291
00:14:28.410 --> 00:14:29.578
Wow.

292
00:14:45.802 --> 00:14:47.220
ANNOUNCER: <i>Merritt McKinney.</i>

293
00:14:48.972 --> 00:14:50.265
<i>Daniel Atlas.</i>

294
00:14:51.641 --> 00:14:52.893
<i>Henley Reeves.</i>

295
00:14:54.895 --> 00:14:56.605
<i>Jack Wilder.</i>

296
00:14:57.397 --> 00:15:01.318
<i>Arthur Tressler and the MGM Grand
proudly presents</i>

297
00:15:04.070 --> 00:15:06.156
<i>The Four Horse men.</i>

298
00:15:06.490 --> 00:15:07.574
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

299
00:15:07.657 --> 00:15:08.825
MERRITT: Thank you.

300
00:15:09.117 --> 00:15:11.328
Tonight we would like to try something

301
00:15:11.411 --> 00:15:13.830
that will. well. set us a bit apart.

302
00:15:13.997 --> 00:15:17.584
For our final trick.
we're gonna do something never before

303
00:15:17.667 --> 00:15:19.669
seen on a Las Vegas stage.

304
00:15:20.670 --> 00:15:23.006
Or any stage for that matter.

305
00:15:23.840 --> 00:15:25.300
Ladies and gentlemen.

306
00:15:27.594 --> 00:15:28.678
tonight

307
00:15:29.596 --> 00:15:31.348
we are going to rob a bank.

308
00:15:31.473 --> 00:15:33.183
(AUDIENCE CHEERING LOUDLY)

309
00:15:42.359 --> 00:15:44.444
That's a lot of excitement for a crime.

310
00:15:45.195 --> 00:15:48.865
HENLEY: I'm getting excited.
What about you. people?

311
00:15:48.949 --> 00:15:50.450
(CHEERING INTENSIFIES)

312
00:15:54.329 --> 00:15:56.540
BOTH: One. two. three!

313
00:16:05.257 --> 00:16:08.510
Sorry. sir. There's absolutely no recording
allowed during the performance.

314
00:16:08.593 --> 00:16:10.178
Oh. yeah. yeah. sure. of course.

315
00:16:10.262 --> 00:16:11.596
- (BEEPS)
- Let me just put this away.

316
00:16:11.846 --> 00:16:13.056
Actually. I need to take that.

317
00:16:13.223 --> 00:16:15.016
After the show. I can come
and give it back to you.

318
00:16:16.393 --> 00:16:17.394
Okay.

319
00:16:18.937 --> 00:16:20.230
(CHUCKLING)

320
00:16:20.897 --> 00:16:22.607
DANIEL: Okay. okay.

321
00:16:22.857 --> 00:16:24.734
Now. please. please. settle down.

322
00:16:25.443 --> 00:16:28.280
Now who here has a bank
they would like us to rob?

323
00:16:29.531 --> 00:16:31.533
That's a lot of people with a vendetta.

324
00:16:31.700 --> 00:16:33.410
So we'll choose one at random then.

325
00:16:33.535 --> 00:16:34.786
(CLAMORING)

326
00:16:35.078 --> 00:16:37.539
My associates will make sure
it's random. Right?

327
00:16:38.581 --> 00:16:40.917
- Elvis. help me out. bud.
- Thank you very much.

328
00:16:41.126 --> 00:16:43.545
In Jack's bowl
are ping pong balls with section numbers.

329
00:16:43.753 --> 00:16:45.755
Jack. could you hand me a section number?

330
00:16:45.964 --> 00:16:47.340
Thank you. We are looking at Section B.

331
00:16:47.549 --> 00:16:49.301
- Where is Section B?
- (CHEERING)

332
00:16:49.384 --> 00:16:51.845
Okay. There.
It's gonna be one of you guys. Get ready.

333
00:16:52.345 --> 00:16:53.680
I don't know why everybody's happy.

334
00:16:53.763 --> 00:16:54.806
It's only them.

335
00:16:55.098 --> 00:16:56.433
Merritt. can I get a row. please?

336
00:16:57.600 --> 00:16:58.643
Thank you. Merritt.

337
00:16:58.727 --> 00:17:00.520
We are looking at row number 5.

338
00:17:00.603 --> 00:17:01.604
Where is that?

339
00:17:01.813 --> 00:17:04.649
And Henley. could I please
have a random seat number?

340
00:17:05.608 --> 00:17:07.110
Oh. Lucky number 13.

341
00:17:07.319 --> 00:17:08.945
- B-5-13. Where are you?
- (AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

342
00:17:09.154 --> 00:17:12.782
Sir. please. stand up. Ah. there you are. Hi.

343
00:17:14.409 --> 00:17:18.204
Could you just confirm for me that this
is. in fact. your seat? B-5-13.

344
00:17:18.288 --> 00:17:19.247
Yes.

345
00:17:19.331 --> 00:17:21.333
Okay. Wonderful.
Now. could you please tell us

346
00:17:21.458 --> 00:17:22.792
your name and the name of your bank?

347
00:17:22.959 --> 00:17:25.170
Well. my name is Etienne Forcier.

348
00:17:25.420 --> 00:17:28.798
And my bank. it's Credit Republicain de Paris.

349
00:17:28.965 --> 00:17:30.133
French. Okay. Uh...

350
00:17:30.342 --> 00:17:31.801
We were hoping for something
a little more local.

351
00:17:31.968 --> 00:17:34.220
a kind of mom-and-pop
credit union with no security.

352
00:17:34.304 --> 00:17:36.264
But that's fine. A promise is a promise.

353
00:17:36.473 --> 00:17:37.640
Could you please come up to the stage

354
00:17:37.724 --> 00:17:39.059
- and we'll rob your bank.
- (CHEERING)

355
00:17:39.142 --> 00:17:41.019
And while he does that...

356
00:17:41.311 --> 00:17:44.439
There is someone here tonight
without whom we would just be

357
00:17:44.522 --> 00:17:47.650
four magicians working the circuit.
trying to get...

358
00:17:47.817 --> 00:17:49.235
Well. actually. trying to get here.

359
00:17:49.319 --> 00:17:52.238
You probably know this man.
if not from one of the many. many

360
00:17:52.322 --> 00:17:53.406
companies he puts his name on.

361
00:17:53.490 --> 00:17:57.118
He is our friend. He is our benefactor.
Mr. Arthur Tressler.

362
00:17:57.202 --> 00:17:59.162
Please. stand up. Art. Please. stand up.

363
00:17:59.371 --> 00:18:02.165
MERRITT: The only man here with
the Queen's cell phone number.

364
00:18:03.124 --> 00:18:05.126
Actually. please. stay standing. Art.

365
00:18:06.169 --> 00:18:08.296
I want to say that when we came
to Mr. Tressler.

366
00:18:08.505 --> 00:18:12.092
we promised that. as a unit. we could become
the biggest name in magic.

367
00:18:12.175 --> 00:18:13.718
HENLEY:So we wanted to say. "Thank you."

368
00:18:13.802 --> 00:18:15.637
And by the way. Art.
you notice on the sign out front.

369
00:18:15.720 --> 00:18:17.639
we made sure we put your name on top.

370
00:18:18.014 --> 00:18:22.102
If you turn out to be as good
as you think you are. dear girl.

371
00:18:22.185 --> 00:18:24.229
that won't be necessary much longer.

372
00:18:24.479 --> 00:18:25.730
HENLEY: We haven't done our closer yet.

373
00:18:25.980 --> 00:18:26.981
- (GRUNTS)
- Why don't you watch it

374
00:18:27.065 --> 00:18:28.274
and then you can decide for yourself.

375
00:18:28.358 --> 00:18:30.610
Ladies and gentlemen. Arthur Tressler!

376
00:18:30.693 --> 00:18:32.362
DANIEL: Thank you.
And. of course. once again.

377
00:18:32.445 --> 00:18:34.406
the Cardinal of Clairvoyance.
Merritt McKinney.

378
00:18:34.906 --> 00:18:38.118
Etienne. what Jack
is bringing to the stage now.

379
00:18:38.201 --> 00:18:41.830
is what we in the magic world
call a teleportation helmet.

380
00:18:42.038 --> 00:18:48.086
You will need to wear this. as it will allow you
to literally fold through space and time

381
00:18:48.336 --> 00:18:50.505
to your bank in the...

382
00:18:50.713 --> 00:18:51.714
8th?

383
00:18:51.923 --> 00:18:53.842
- 9th arrondissement.
- Yeah.

384
00:18:54.050 --> 00:18:58.012
Now. once you are there. we will be able
to speak with you through this helmet.

385
00:18:58.096 --> 00:18:59.848
- Now if... Ah!
- Ow.

386
00:19:00.056 --> 00:19:01.724
- Oh. my God. that's beautiful.
- (AUDIENCE CHUCKLING)

387
00:19:01.891 --> 00:19:04.686
It has the added attraction of being
very stylish.

388
00:19:04.769 --> 00:19:08.231
It's about time the French learned
from America on that subject.

389
00:19:09.566 --> 00:19:10.692
Is that a beautiful piece of headgear?

390
00:19:10.775 --> 00:19:12.402
- Thank you. Thank you...
- It is.

391
00:19:13.445 --> 00:19:16.030
Thank you. Thank you very much.

392
00:19:16.114 --> 00:19:17.323
MERRITT: <i>Mais oui. Mais oui.</i>

393
00:19:17.407 --> 00:19:18.741
But before you go anywhere.

394
00:19:18.867 --> 00:19:20.994
could you please. pick a card. any card.

395
00:19:21.077 --> 00:19:22.078
Not that card. Oh!

396
00:19:22.412 --> 00:19:25.832
No. that's an old American joke.
You can take that one.

397
00:19:25.915 --> 00:19:27.375
Okay. This one?

398
00:19:27.584 --> 00:19:29.544
Show it to your friends in Section B.
But not to us.

399
00:19:31.379 --> 00:19:33.381
Okay. great.
Now if you could just sign your name there.

400
00:19:33.465 --> 00:19:35.884
- Yes.
- In English. if possible.

401
00:19:36.259 --> 00:19:37.635
- MERRITT: That's good.
- Thanks.

402
00:19:38.761 --> 00:19:39.888
Put it in your pocket.

403
00:19:40.263 --> 00:19:42.640
And now for one tiny detail.

404
00:19:44.100 --> 00:19:46.227
(AUDIENCE GASPING)

405
00:19:50.940 --> 00:19:52.484
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

406
00:20:00.074 --> 00:20:04.621
Now. Etienne. let's step into
this cockamamie contraption.

407
00:20:04.829 --> 00:20:06.748
And I'll step off of it. <i>Boone chance.</i>

408
00:20:07.165 --> 00:20:10.043
It's 11 :50 p.m. here in Vegas.

409
00:20:10.126 --> 00:20:14.797
That's 8:50 a.m. in Paris.
Your bank opens in less than 10 minutes.

410
00:20:15.006 --> 00:20:16.049
One.

411
00:20:16.132 --> 00:20:17.175
two...

412
00:20:17.258 --> 00:20:18.301
Three.

413
00:20:20.136 --> 00:20:21.179
(ALL GASPING)

414
00:20:21.596 --> 00:20:22.805
MERRITT: What the fuck?

415
00:20:22.972 --> 00:20:24.599
- Wow! Etienne?
- Whoa. Etienne?

416
00:20:24.807 --> 00:20:26.643
It wasn't supposed to happen
like that. was it?

417
00:20:26.809 --> 00:20:27.852
HENLEY: Etienne?

418
00:20:28.478 --> 00:20:30.480
I liked that little French guy.

419
00:20:30.647 --> 00:20:31.689
Where did he go?

420
00:20:31.814 --> 00:20:33.316
(CARS HONKING)

421
00:20:40.657 --> 00:20:42.200
Wait. there he is.

422
00:20:44.494 --> 00:20:46.538
No. no. no. no. please. please. please.

423
00:20:46.788 --> 00:20:48.665
This is Daniel Atlas. Can you hear me?

424
00:20:49.541 --> 00:20:51.960
- Etienne? Are you okay?
- <i>Yes.</i>

425
00:20:52.043 --> 00:20:54.420
Perfect. What do you see in there?

426
00:20:56.381 --> 00:20:57.507
Money.

427
00:20:58.007 --> 00:20:59.008
Is this real?

428
00:20:59.175 --> 00:21:01.678
Yes. Looks like three million or so
Euros' worth.

429
00:21:02.387 --> 00:21:03.680
(SPEAKS FRENCH)

430
00:21:03.888 --> 00:21:05.640
Okay. now. here's what
we're gonna need you to do.

431
00:21:05.723 --> 00:21:09.227
<i>I want you to take the card that you signed
out of your pocket.</i>

432
00:21:09.352 --> 00:21:11.521
And I want you to take the ticket stub
from tonight's show

433
00:21:11.729 --> 00:21:13.898
<i>and I want you to put it right there
in the middle of the money.</i>

434
00:21:18.027 --> 00:21:19.195
Now drop it.

435
00:21:31.207 --> 00:21:34.335
Now. on the side of your helmet
you should feel a button.

436
00:21:34.544 --> 00:21:35.712
Don't press it just yet.

437
00:21:35.920 --> 00:21:40.508
That button activates an air duct
that connects Paris to Las Vegas.

438
00:21:40.717 --> 00:21:42.051
<i>Okay. good. Now you can press it.</i>

439
00:21:42.218 --> 00:21:45.763
All right. now. Etienne. hold on tight.
You might feel a bit of a vacuum.

440
00:21:45.847 --> 00:21:46.848
(CHUCKLES)

441
00:21:48.099 --> 00:21:49.767
(AIR WHOOSHING)

442
00:21:54.439 --> 00:21:55.565
(WHOOPS)

443
00:22:03.740 --> 00:22:05.366
Whoo! (LAUGHING)

444
00:22:16.919 --> 00:22:18.254
Oh. Wait a second.

445
00:22:18.463 --> 00:22:19.881
- Huh.
- (RUMBLING)

446
00:22:31.059 --> 00:22:32.560
WOMAN: <i>Oh. merde.</i>

447
00:22:32.977 --> 00:22:34.604
(CHEERING)

448
00:22:52.246 --> 00:22:53.414
(CHUCKLES)

449
00:22:57.418 --> 00:22:58.628
(LAUGHING)

450
00:23:11.974 --> 00:23:13.810
Thank you. Etienne. Thank you. everyone!

451
00:23:14.310 --> 00:23:15.436
We are The Four Horsemen.

452
00:23:15.645 --> 00:23:17.939
- And good night!
- Good night!

453
00:23:26.489 --> 00:23:27.949
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

454
00:23:30.743 --> 00:23:31.953
Hold up here.

455
00:23:32.328 --> 00:23:33.621
Dylan Rhodes.

456
00:23:35.415 --> 00:23:37.417
What? I don't think I heard you correctly.

457
00:23:37.625 --> 00:23:38.960
Did you say magicians?

458
00:23:39.168 --> 00:23:40.795
Yeah. Dylan. magicians.

459
00:23:41.170 --> 00:23:42.255
<i>Where are you now?</i>

460
00:23:42.463 --> 00:23:44.340
I'm at Aria.
I'm heading up there to grab 'em now.

461
00:23:48.678 --> 00:23:50.471
FBI! Hands where I can see them.

462
00:23:50.680 --> 00:23:51.973
Let's go. Get 'em up. Come on.

463
00:23:52.140 --> 00:23:53.141
<i>Uno minuto.</i>

464
00:23:53.433 --> 00:23:55.143
FULLER: Let's go. Get 'em up.

465
00:23:55.351 --> 00:23:56.644
Put the book down.

466
00:23:56.853 --> 00:23:58.479
Okay. You got me.

467
00:23:58.688 --> 00:24:00.106
- Freeze! Hands in the air!
- HENLEY: (GASPS) Oh. my!

468
00:24:00.690 --> 00:24:03.443
Do one of you guys
mind giving us a hand with our bags?

469
00:24:03.985 --> 00:24:04.986
Let's go.

470
00:24:10.658 --> 00:24:12.285
(PEOPLE APPLAUDING)

471
00:24:22.837 --> 00:24:24.672
DYLAN: <i>Boss. please tell me this is a joke.</i>

472
00:24:24.881 --> 00:24:27.800
<i>I just got Willy Mears
to finger Paulie Attanasio.</i>

473
00:24:28.009 --> 00:24:31.262
I'm a month. two tops.
away from blowing this whole thing open.

474
00:24:31.345 --> 00:24:33.514
- Get Turkelson.
- He's in Atlantic City.

475
00:24:33.681 --> 00:24:36.392
What about Cowan? Look at him.
He's just sitting there on his ass.

476
00:24:36.517 --> 00:24:37.727
Hilarious. Rhodes.

477
00:24:38.186 --> 00:24:39.312
I love you.

478
00:24:39.645 --> 00:24:40.688
Asshole.

479
00:24:40.897 --> 00:24:42.315
I don't have time for this magic crap.

480
00:24:42.523 --> 00:24:45.067
This crap just pulled
three million Euro out of a Parisian bank.

481
00:24:45.151 --> 00:24:46.235
- That's how much they got?
- Yeah.

482
00:24:46.402 --> 00:24:47.904
Actually. 3.2.

483
00:24:51.908 --> 00:24:53.284
- Who is she?
- (MUMBLES)

484
00:24:53.576 --> 00:24:54.577
Who are you?

485
00:24:54.660 --> 00:24:57.830
Alma Dray from Interpol.
I'll be working the investigation with you.

486
00:24:58.039 --> 00:24:59.081
You gotta be kidding me.

487
00:24:59.290 --> 00:25:02.001
It's bad enough they got me chasing down
David Copperfield and Friends.

488
00:25:02.210 --> 00:25:05.296
Now I'm being saddled with.
no offense. with Interpol?

489
00:25:05.505 --> 00:25:07.590
I look forward to working
with you. too. Agent Rhodes.

490
00:25:07.799 --> 00:25:10.676
I'm sorry. I don't think I'm gonna
need your help on this. Okay?

491
00:25:10.885 --> 00:25:12.887
- Where's the French guy?
- I already spoke to him.

492
00:25:13.513 --> 00:25:15.890
Oh. you did?
You spoke to my witness before me?

493
00:25:16.098 --> 00:25:19.101
Your witness?
I thought you didn't want the case.

494
00:25:19.310 --> 00:25:20.895
Besides. he's useless.

495
00:25:21.103 --> 00:25:22.647
Oh. really? Why is that?

496
00:25:22.855 --> 00:25:25.024
Because he believes their magic was real.

497
00:25:25.233 --> 00:25:28.277
Oh. he believes the magic was real?
You're right. he probably is useless.

498
00:25:28.486 --> 00:25:31.405
Is it okay with Interpol if we talk to him. too?

499
00:25:31.489 --> 00:25:33.074
- Mm-hmm.
- Thank you.

500
00:25:34.116 --> 00:25:37.203
I have never stolen a thing in my life. okay?

501
00:25:37.411 --> 00:25:39.622
I tried to give the money back.
but they won't take it.

502
00:25:39.872 --> 00:25:42.333
Okay. okay. okay.
let's just say you robbed a bank.

503
00:25:42.416 --> 00:25:43.584
I did.

504
00:25:43.751 --> 00:25:44.961
Fine. Fantastic. You did.

505
00:25:45.086 --> 00:25:47.630
But since I'm new to this.
can you explain to me how you went

506
00:25:47.713 --> 00:25:50.132
from Las Vegas to Paris in three seconds?

507
00:25:50.550 --> 00:25:52.677
With the teleportation helmet.

508
00:25:52.927 --> 00:25:54.345
Okay. what the hell is going on here?

509
00:25:54.470 --> 00:25:56.138
He was hypnotized during the show.

510
00:25:56.597 --> 00:25:58.307
I told you. he's useless.

511
00:25:58.391 --> 00:26:01.185
Okay. I'll deal with you when I'm done
with this other bullshit.

512
00:26:02.144 --> 00:26:03.771
(CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING)

513
00:26:04.605 --> 00:26:05.690
Hey!

514
00:26:05.773 --> 00:26:07.567
FULLER: During the show.
half the audience was hypnotized

515
00:26:07.650 --> 00:26:09.068
to believe they were in the Philharmonic.

516
00:26:09.277 --> 00:26:11.571
I guess that "bullshit" was the trigger word.

517
00:26:11.654 --> 00:26:14.782
Okay. Hey. hey. <i>Écoutez.</i>
Etienne. come on down from there.

518
00:26:14.866 --> 00:26:15.950
You're not in the Philharmonic.

519
00:26:16.242 --> 00:26:18.661
- How do you say "stop" in French?
- Stop.

520
00:26:18.870 --> 00:26:19.871
Tell him to stop.

521
00:26:20.079 --> 00:26:24.250
No. I can't.
You just have to let him finish his movement.

522
00:26:24.458 --> 00:26:26.210
Okay. I need a time-out.

523
00:26:26.335 --> 00:26:27.837
Too many French people in one room.

524
00:26:27.962 --> 00:26:29.463
- Agent Rhodes!
- Huh?

525
00:26:29.547 --> 00:26:32.133
I'm ordered by my bosses to provide a report.

526
00:26:32.341 --> 00:26:35.303
And until we have one. I'm here. like it or not.

527
00:26:35.469 --> 00:26:37.179
So we can work together.

528
00:26:37.305 --> 00:26:41.434
or you can continue to follow behind
asking the same exact questions I'm asking.

529
00:26:41.517 --> 00:26:42.685
It's up to you.

530
00:26:42.977 --> 00:26:44.312
(SNORING)

531
00:26:45.354 --> 00:26:46.397
Hmm.

532
00:26:46.480 --> 00:26:47.690
I'm not finished.

533
00:26:47.940 --> 00:26:51.652
I just flew 12 hours.
after what was already a long day.

534
00:26:51.819 --> 00:26:53.821
And I do not handle jet lag well.

535
00:26:57.283 --> 00:26:59.660
So if you want to see who can be grumpier.

536
00:26:59.785 --> 00:27:01.871
- I promise you. you will lose.
- Hmm.

537
00:27:02.830 --> 00:27:07.084
Mm-hmm. Fine. So which one of these idiots
do you want to talk to first?

538
00:27:07.168 --> 00:27:08.210
Him?

539
00:27:13.841 --> 00:27:14.926
Dylan. for the record.

540
00:27:15.051 --> 00:27:17.219
mentalism has never actually
been proven to be accurate.

541
00:27:17.303 --> 00:27:18.304
Okay.

542
00:27:18.387 --> 00:27:21.182
That is to say. that it's not a science.
It's more for entertainment.

543
00:27:21.265 --> 00:27:22.266
All right.

544
00:27:22.350 --> 00:27:25.728
Just don't believe everything the guy says.
That's all.

545
00:27:26.938 --> 00:27:31.525
Please convey my deepest apologies
to your colleague out there.

546
00:27:31.692 --> 00:27:34.070
I'm really sorry about this
whole Tranny Tuesday thing.

547
00:27:34.195 --> 00:27:35.237
I was out of line.

548
00:27:35.446 --> 00:27:36.572
Tranny Tuesday?

549
00:27:36.739 --> 00:27:38.449
Well. it's an arrangement
he and his wife have.

550
00:27:38.532 --> 00:27:40.284
Or might not have. if you believe

551
00:27:40.368 --> 00:27:42.703
everything Agent Fuller
is saying to be correct.

552
00:27:42.870 --> 00:27:47.458
But isn't there a proud tradition in the FBI
of men wearing dresses?

553
00:27:48.209 --> 00:27:51.879
<i>No shame. Agent Fuller. No shame.</i>

554
00:27:53.714 --> 00:27:56.467
(LAUGHS) I'm just having fun.

555
00:27:56.592 --> 00:27:58.928
Was this your card? No.

556
00:27:59.011 --> 00:28:00.304
See. I knew you weren't
a queen of hearts lady.

557
00:28:00.388 --> 00:28:01.389
and I respect that.

558
00:28:01.472 --> 00:28:03.349
The trick usually works better
when I'm not strapped in here.

559
00:28:03.432 --> 00:28:04.475
but I understand protocol.

560
00:28:04.558 --> 00:28:05.810
Okay. okay.

561
00:28:06.018 --> 00:28:08.604
So. if you had nothing to do with it.

562
00:28:08.688 --> 00:28:11.107
then how did
the playing card get into the vault?

563
00:28:11.357 --> 00:28:12.358
Oh. yes. That would be...

564
00:28:12.441 --> 00:28:13.943
What do the kids call it these days?

565
00:28:14.068 --> 00:28:15.194
Oh. yes. that's right. Magic.

566
00:28:15.277 --> 00:28:17.113
Just answer the question. okay. smartass.

567
00:28:17.363 --> 00:28:20.408
All right. Sorry. sorry. sorry.

568
00:28:20.950 --> 00:28:22.910
You can keep that. Don't share it with him.

569
00:28:23.077 --> 00:28:26.080
It says here you are a mentalist.

570
00:28:26.288 --> 00:28:29.250
- Hmm.
- What exactly is mentalism?

571
00:28:29.458 --> 00:28:32.420
Tricks. mostly. Um. some science.

572
00:28:32.586 --> 00:28:36.424
Targeted guessing
might be a most apt description.

573
00:28:36.632 --> 00:28:39.885
Along with some intuition
and the occasional...

574
00:28:41.554 --> 00:28:43.222
Voices in my head.

575
00:28:43.389 --> 00:28:44.348
(LAUGHS)

576
00:28:44.432 --> 00:28:46.142
Says here you were fairly famous at one point.

577
00:28:46.434 --> 00:28:47.435
Mm-hmm.

578
00:28:47.560 --> 00:28:49.437
You can
even hypnotize people over the phone.

579
00:28:49.603 --> 00:28:52.148
Some big tours
around the U.S. for a few years.

580
00:28:52.231 --> 00:28:54.233
- two TV specials.
- Glory days.

581
00:28:54.316 --> 00:28:57.778
Then your brother/manager disappeared
with all your hard-earned money.

582
00:28:57.987 --> 00:28:59.238
(CLEARS THROAT)
Did your research. did you?

583
00:28:59.405 --> 00:29:01.115
DYLAN: IRS audit. Back taxes.

584
00:29:01.323 --> 00:29:05.453
You've had a long hard slog back
into the limelight. haven't you. Mr. McKinney?

585
00:29:05.661 --> 00:29:10.332
Yes. indeed. it has. And I do appreciate
that trip down Memory Lane.

586
00:29:10.583 --> 00:29:12.543
As far as I understand it.
when the man from Paris

587
00:29:12.626 --> 00:29:13.753
put on the magical helmet...

588
00:29:13.836 --> 00:29:14.837
Listen to me.

589
00:29:14.962 --> 00:29:17.423
If you didn't rob that bank.
then you knew about it.

590
00:29:17.631 --> 00:29:18.716
Which makes you an accomplice.

591
00:29:18.799 --> 00:29:21.218
So if you wanna walk out of here today.
I'd suggest you start...

592
00:29:21.302 --> 00:29:23.888
Now you listen to me. unless you think
there's a D.A. in the state of Nevada

593
00:29:23.971 --> 00:29:25.306
who'd be willing
to make sense of this to a jury.

594
00:29:25.473 --> 00:29:26.640
then we have a show to perform.

595
00:29:26.849 --> 00:29:29.310
And you. Agent Rhodes.
have a drawing board to get back to.

596
00:29:29.435 --> 00:29:30.853
Is this your first date?

597
00:29:31.979 --> 00:29:32.980
What?

598
00:29:33.147 --> 00:29:36.942
No. I mean. obviously. you guys don't
know each other well. if at all.

599
00:29:37.026 --> 00:29:40.571
But. like.
there is a palpable tension in this room.

600
00:29:40.654 --> 00:29:42.323
And before you get involved.

601
00:29:42.531 --> 00:29:45.993
you should consider the fact
that she has a lot of big secrets.

602
00:29:46.160 --> 00:29:51.040
And I know the first one is that
this is your first time off the desk. Isn't it?

603
00:29:51.499 --> 00:29:52.917
You should have said something to him.

604
00:29:53.000 --> 00:29:55.044
This is a weird way for you to find out.

605
00:29:55.294 --> 00:29:57.129
You are literally begging to be arrested.
You know that?

606
00:29:57.213 --> 00:29:59.548
If it means you would actually do it.
then. yeah. But you won't.

607
00:29:59.673 --> 00:30:03.260
Because if you did. it means that you.
and the FBI. and your friends at Interpol.

608
00:30:03.344 --> 00:30:06.847
actually believe.
at an institutional level. in magic.

609
00:30:07.890 --> 00:30:09.517
The press would have a field day.

610
00:30:09.725 --> 00:30:11.393
And we'd be even more famous
than we already are.

611
00:30:11.644 --> 00:30:14.146
And you guys would look like idiots
even more then you already are.

612
00:30:14.355 --> 00:30:16.190
Well. no. not you. But him. Right?

613
00:30:17.191 --> 00:30:19.527
You have.
what we in the business. like to call.

614
00:30:19.610 --> 00:30:21.028
"nothing up your sleeve."

615
00:30:21.195 --> 00:30:22.196
And you know it.

616
00:30:22.363 --> 00:30:28.035
Don't draw him in and then dump him
because abandonment is a big "area" for him.

617
00:30:28.536 --> 00:30:29.537
Mommy?

618
00:30:30.371 --> 00:30:31.622
Daddy.

619
00:30:31.956 --> 00:30:33.165
Ah! You have big daddy issues.

620
00:30:33.499 --> 00:30:35.042
- Okay. that's enough.
- I'll tell you what.

621
00:30:35.126 --> 00:30:38.379
Your average therapist is gonna charge you
$200-$300 for this sesh.

622
00:30:38.504 --> 00:30:40.339
Me? I'll take a tenner.

623
00:30:41.340 --> 00:30:43.717
Okay. later. if you're feeling magnanimous...

624
00:30:44.510 --> 00:30:45.970
I'll still take a tenner.

625
00:30:46.679 --> 00:30:48.722
You wanna know who sat
in that chair before you?

626
00:30:48.848 --> 00:30:50.891
Mob bosses. murderers. and thieves.

627
00:30:51.142 --> 00:30:52.393
And you know who put them there?

628
00:30:52.643 --> 00:30:54.395
The guy who's sitting in this chair.

629
00:30:54.645 --> 00:30:58.482
So I warn you.
I can maintain my resolve much longer

630
00:30:58.691 --> 00:31:01.402
than you can maintain that phony arrogance.

631
00:31:01.569 --> 00:31:06.407
And the instant that you even show
the slightest crack in that smug facade.

632
00:31:06.574 --> 00:31:07.741
I'll be there.

633
00:31:07.908 --> 00:31:09.493
I will be all over you like...

634
00:31:09.577 --> 00:31:10.744
Like white on rice?

635
00:31:11.078 --> 00:31:12.580
Sorry. That's unfair.

636
00:31:12.746 --> 00:31:14.915
Let me warn you. I want you to follow.

637
00:31:15.166 --> 00:31:16.500
Because no matter
what you think you might know.

638
00:31:16.584 --> 00:31:19.253
we will always be one step. three steps.
seven steps ahead of you.

639
00:31:19.336 --> 00:31:20.462
And just when you think you're catching up.

640
00:31:20.546 --> 00:31:21.881
that's when we'll be right behind you.

641
00:31:22.089 --> 00:31:23.507
And at no time will you be
anywhere other than

642
00:31:23.591 --> 00:31:24.675
exactly where I want you to be.

643
00:31:24.758 --> 00:31:27.845
So come close. Get all over me
because the closer you think you are.

644
00:31:27.928 --> 00:31:29.263
the less you'll actually see.

645
00:31:29.430 --> 00:31:30.890
- I'm gonna nail you...
- (GRUNTS)

646
00:31:34.894 --> 00:31:36.604
Something wrong with that soda. Miss?

647
00:31:38.522 --> 00:31:39.607
(RATTLING)

648
00:31:40.858 --> 00:31:41.942
(CAN OPENS)

649
00:31:45.529 --> 00:31:46.780
Oh! Shit!

650
00:31:47.364 --> 00:31:48.866
First rule of magic.

651
00:31:49.700 --> 00:31:51.952
Always be the smartest guy in the room.

652
00:32:14.975 --> 00:32:16.852
Boss. what are we doing?
We're letting them go?

653
00:32:17.061 --> 00:32:18.979
They all but admitted
they're gonna do it again.

654
00:32:19.188 --> 00:32:21.065
About a half an hour ago.
you didn't give a damn about them.

655
00:32:21.315 --> 00:32:23.067
- What changed?
- I met them.

656
00:32:23.150 --> 00:32:24.151
Hey. Guys.

657
00:32:24.485 --> 00:32:26.654
Hey. I ran a check on the audience.

658
00:32:27.029 --> 00:32:28.155
Most of it was just filler.

659
00:32:28.239 --> 00:32:29.907
People that Tressler
dragged in to pack the room.

660
00:32:29.990 --> 00:32:33.035
But guess who was sitting there in the back.
filming the whole damn thing?

661
00:32:33.160 --> 00:32:34.161
I don't know.

662
00:32:34.245 --> 00:32:35.704
Thaddeus Bradley.

663
00:32:38.165 --> 00:32:40.334
Thaddeus Bradley.
the guy from TV with the DVDs and shows?

664
00:32:40.459 --> 00:32:41.418
No.

665
00:32:41.502 --> 00:32:43.671
Okay. well. he debunks magicians.

666
00:32:43.921 --> 00:32:45.756
He exposes them.
He shows you how to do their tricks.

667
00:32:45.839 --> 00:32:46.924
Get him on the phone.

668
00:32:47.007 --> 00:32:49.885
- I did. You're having lunch with him in 45.
- Good.

669
00:32:50.052 --> 00:32:52.721
WOMAN: <i>Mr. Bradley started as a magician.</i>

670
00:32:52.805 --> 00:32:54.515
- He was actually quite good.
- Really?

671
00:32:54.848 --> 00:32:56.976
- One of the best.
- You don't say.

672
00:32:58.310 --> 00:33:01.188
"The greatest genius
is in seeing through the illusion."

673
00:33:01.272 --> 00:33:03.691
That's a man who loves his work.

674
00:33:05.150 --> 00:33:06.944
You sure I can't interest you
in a glass of wine?

675
00:33:07.027 --> 00:33:09.863
No. no. no. No. thank you. sir. We're working.

676
00:33:10.322 --> 00:33:11.490
I will take one.

677
00:33:20.040 --> 00:33:22.584
That's incredible. That's amazing.

678
00:33:24.211 --> 00:33:25.379
Red dye. palmed.

679
00:33:25.462 --> 00:33:28.132
Is that how Jesus did it? That's incredible.

680
00:33:28.215 --> 00:33:29.550
I'm sorry. Can I just take a minute here?

681
00:33:29.633 --> 00:33:31.927
You were one of the great magicians.
Why did you stop?

682
00:33:32.553 --> 00:33:35.222
Do you know how many people
went to see magic performed live

683
00:33:35.306 --> 00:33:36.890
in the last half decade?

684
00:33:36.974 --> 00:33:38.225
About 1 .6 million.

685
00:33:38.309 --> 00:33:41.645
You know how many DVDs I sold
in the same period?

686
00:33:41.729 --> 00:33:43.022
Five million.

687
00:33:43.105 --> 00:33:44.148
Right. so it's about the money.

688
00:33:44.231 --> 00:33:45.733
Well. the money is only there

689
00:33:45.858 --> 00:33:49.111
because the need to know
is greater than the desire to be fooled.

690
00:33:49.194 --> 00:33:53.490
Like you. I detest those
who prey upon the gullibility of the masses.

691
00:33:53.574 --> 00:33:57.244
With all due respect.
isn't there a cost. though. to this game?

692
00:33:57.786 --> 00:33:58.829
Cost?

693
00:33:58.912 --> 00:34:00.205
I don't know. Careers.

694
00:34:00.289 --> 00:34:01.415
Lives.

695
00:34:01.498 --> 00:34:04.710
I assume you're referring to Lionel Shrike.

696
00:34:05.169 --> 00:34:07.004
I'm sorry. who?

697
00:34:07.087 --> 00:34:08.589
Lionel Shrike.

698
00:34:08.672 --> 00:34:12.968
A middling magician who drowned
in the Hudson River 30 years ago.

699
00:34:13.093 --> 00:34:16.847
On Mr. Bradley's first special.
he revealed all of Shrike's tricks.

700
00:34:16.930 --> 00:34:20.434
The next year.
Shrike tried to stage a comeback.

701
00:34:20.517 --> 00:34:23.854
He was shackled inside a safe.
and dropped into the river.

702
00:34:23.937 --> 00:34:25.064
But he never resurfaced.

703
00:34:25.147 --> 00:34:27.399
You mean he died?

704
00:34:27.483 --> 00:34:29.276
I didn't kill him.

705
00:34:29.360 --> 00:34:33.614
He killed himself trying to do something
he wasn't prepared to handle.

706
00:34:33.697 --> 00:34:35.908
You do realize this is a game?

707
00:34:35.991 --> 00:34:37.785
Believe me. it's not a game.

708
00:34:37.868 --> 00:34:39.036
It is a game.

709
00:34:39.119 --> 00:34:40.871
You're the game. You're being played.

710
00:34:40.954 --> 00:34:44.333
And your pathetic attempts
at fawning to gain my trust...

711
00:34:44.458 --> 00:34:46.210
I mean. come on.

712
00:34:46.293 --> 00:34:47.294
You got me.

713
00:34:47.378 --> 00:34:48.629
If you really want to know

714
00:34:48.712 --> 00:34:52.508
how a bank in Paris was robbed
from a stage in Las Vegas.

715
00:34:52.591 --> 00:34:54.551
my special comes out next month.

716
00:34:54.635 --> 00:34:55.761
Or I could just bring you in

717
00:34:55.844 --> 00:34:58.305
on obstruction charges
and force you to tell me.

718
00:34:58.389 --> 00:34:59.932
Unless. of course.
what you're trying to say to me is that

719
00:35:00.015 --> 00:35:03.102
you actually don't know how they did it.

720
00:35:05.062 --> 00:35:07.231
Showmanship and theatrics.

721
00:35:07.439 --> 00:35:09.566
When a magician waves his hand and says.

722
00:35:09.775 --> 00:35:11.485
"This is where the magic is happening."

723
00:35:11.568 --> 00:35:13.946
The real trick is happening somewhere else.

724
00:35:14.446 --> 00:35:17.407
Misdirection. A basic concept of magic.

725
00:35:17.616 --> 00:35:19.910
Not interested in the concepts of magic.

726
00:35:20.077 --> 00:35:21.578
I wanna know how they robbed a bank.

727
00:35:21.745 --> 00:35:24.456
You're an idiot if you think
they robbed a bank.

728
00:35:24.706 --> 00:35:25.958
But don't take my word for it.

729
00:35:26.458 --> 00:35:28.127
How about a trip to Paris?

730
00:35:28.585 --> 00:35:31.630
Hermia. the teleportation helmet.
please. darling?

731
00:35:32.256 --> 00:35:33.590
You're joking. right?

732
00:35:33.757 --> 00:35:35.592
You wanna know how they did it or not?

733
00:35:36.760 --> 00:35:38.762
I'm just gonna put this on your head.

734
00:35:40.139 --> 00:35:41.473
THADDEUS: Step right up.

735
00:35:42.724 --> 00:35:44.059
There you go.

736
00:35:45.102 --> 00:35:48.730
Now we just pull this down all safe and snug.

737
00:35:49.773 --> 00:35:52.442
Make yourself comfortable. There we go.

738
00:35:52.901 --> 00:35:57.156
And when you're ready to go to Paris.
just say the magic word.

739
00:35:57.322 --> 00:35:58.323
Blow me?

740
00:35:59.575 --> 00:36:01.326
- That'll suffice.
- <i>Bon voyage.</i>

741
00:36:04.663 --> 00:36:05.831
(SCREAMING)

742
00:36:12.296 --> 00:36:13.589
THADDEUS: <i>Bonjour.</i>

743
00:36:13.672 --> 00:36:16.800
I personally prefer to take the stairs to Paris.

744
00:36:17.301 --> 00:36:19.219
Welcome to the City of Light. Agent Rhodes.

745
00:36:19.303 --> 00:36:21.054
Hardy har har. What was with the helmet?

746
00:36:21.722 --> 00:36:22.806
My fun.

747
00:36:23.765 --> 00:36:25.184
- (LAUGHS)
- What?

748
00:36:25.642 --> 00:36:26.727
- Nothing.
- Oh!

749
00:36:28.645 --> 00:36:30.397
- So they got a vault set.
- Yes.

750
00:36:30.480 --> 00:36:33.317
And it's the exact replica
of the little French guy's bank.

751
