00:46:59.234 --> 00:47:02.904
do you really think it's possible
there's a fifth Horseman?

988
00:47:04.364 --> 00:47:05.657
Yeah.

989
00:47:07.450 --> 00:47:09.244
(EERIE MUSIC PLAYING)

990
00:47:12.080 --> 00:47:13.998
THADDEUS: <i>There is a legend
of a secret order</i>

991
00:47:14.082 --> 00:47:15.959
<i>born in ancient Egypt called</i>

992
00:47:16.417 --> 00:47:17.502
<i>"The Eye."</i>

993
00:47:19.379 --> 00:47:24.050
<i>It is said they perfected sleight of hand
to steal food from the Pharaohs</i>

994
00:47:24.133 --> 00:47:25.885
<i>and give it to the slaves.</i>

995
00:47:26.302 --> 00:47:27.303
<i>Their purpose?</i>

996
00:47:27.595 --> 00:47:31.599
<i>Using magic and illusion
to even the scales of justice.</i>

997
00:47:32.475 --> 00:47:36.813
<i>Are The Horsemen next in a long line
of fools to believe this myth?</i>

998
00:47:37.188 --> 00:47:41.943
Will they evade the rules of law and logic
like they did in Las Vegas?

999
00:47:42.735 --> 00:47:47.031
Or will the dark mysticism
of this Southern swampland

1000
00:47:47.574 --> 00:47:49.033
get the better of them?

1001
00:47:49.200 --> 00:47:51.452
(SLOW CLAPPING)

1002
00:47:55.623 --> 00:47:57.083
Bravo. Mr. Bradley.

1003
00:47:57.166 --> 00:48:01.671
Either you have a cease-and-desist.
which you don't. or you should leave.

1004
00:48:01.754 --> 00:48:05.550
If I want something to cease or desist.

1005
00:48:06.801 --> 00:48:07.969
it does.

1006
00:48:08.052 --> 00:48:09.053
Take five.

1007
00:48:09.679 --> 00:48:11.514
According to your potential backers.

1008
00:48:11.598 --> 00:48:15.184
you stand to make 2.5 million tops

1009
00:48:15.476 --> 00:48:17.020
from your best special.

1010
00:48:17.228 --> 00:48:19.897
I have here a check

1011
00:48:21.649 --> 00:48:22.900
for 3.5 million.

1012
00:48:23.109 --> 00:48:24.068
To walk away?

1013
00:48:24.152 --> 00:48:27.864
To fly away. My jet is at your disposal.

1014
00:48:30.116 --> 00:48:32.785
Let's not kid ourselves. Mr. Tressler.

1015
00:48:34.412 --> 00:48:36.497
You're in this to ride them up.

1016
00:48:36.998 --> 00:48:38.958
I'm in it to ride them down.

1017
00:48:39.292 --> 00:48:42.337
I take it that we do not have a deal.

1018
00:48:43.838 --> 00:48:48.176
And therein lies our conflict.

1019
00:48:51.596 --> 00:48:52.847
Let me be blunt.

1020
00:48:53.264 --> 00:48:57.727
My bank account is much.
much bigger than yours.

1021
00:48:57.935 --> 00:49:00.772
And my lawyers are much stronger.

1022
00:49:01.105 --> 00:49:04.192
And they will manacle you

1023
00:49:05.443 --> 00:49:07.111
with so many injunctions.

1024
00:49:07.528 --> 00:49:12.533
Until you stand by. hopelessly watching
everything that you own drain away

1025
00:49:13.368 --> 00:49:15.745
in front of your greedy little eyes.

1026
00:49:15.953 --> 00:49:18.247
This isn't the first time I've been threatened.

1027
00:49:19.707 --> 00:49:21.125
And I'm still here.

1028
00:49:21.209 --> 00:49:25.713
It is. however.
the first time you've been threatened by me.

1029
00:49:26.506 --> 00:49:30.927
And if you do anything
to sully my investment.

1030
00:49:31.010 --> 00:49:33.388
the ride down. which you mentioned.

1031
00:49:33.471 --> 00:49:38.434
will be sudden. precipitous.
and measurable on the Richter scale.

1032
00:49:40.228 --> 00:49:42.146
Oops. You shouldn't have done that.

1033
00:49:43.648 --> 00:49:45.191
According to superstition.

1034
00:49:45.400 --> 00:49:48.319
one who uses a doll to enact one's own wrath.

1035
00:49:48.528 --> 00:49:52.990
is likely to bring that very wrath unto himself.

1036
00:49:53.825 --> 00:49:55.326
Isn't that funny?

1037
00:49:56.160 --> 00:49:57.995
And I thought you didn't believe in magic.

1038
00:50:01.791 --> 00:50:04.085
(ALL CLAMORING)

1039
00:50:08.047 --> 00:50:09.132
Do me a favor.

1040
00:50:09.215 --> 00:50:13.302
Visualize your most adventurous
sexual experience.

1041
00:50:13.386 --> 00:50:14.387
Stay out of my head. you perv.

1042
00:50:14.470 --> 00:50:18.182
Well. no. if I stay out of your head.
I'm never gonna get into your pants.

1043
00:50:18.266 --> 00:50:20.309
- Right.
- So let's stick with this exercise.

1044
00:50:20.393 --> 00:50:22.270
- And it helps...
- THADDEUS: Pardon the intrusion.

1045
00:50:22.353 --> 00:50:24.939
I just wanted to wish you good luck tonight.

1046
00:50:25.022 --> 00:50:27.608
What. so you can try to expose us later
on your little website?

1047
00:50:27.692 --> 00:50:28.860
And on demand.

1048
00:50:28.943 --> 00:50:30.403
That's not gonna happen.

1049
00:50:30.528 --> 00:50:31.946
Oh. no?

1050
00:50:32.029 --> 00:50:35.032
Operating on a special plane
because of The Eye?

1051
00:50:35.742 --> 00:50:40.538
I heard it's a lovely place.
Lots of star shine and moonbeams.

1052
00:50:40.621 --> 00:50:43.082
Make any magician's wish come true.

1053
00:50:43.166 --> 00:50:44.584
You've come a long way.

1054
00:50:44.667 --> 00:50:46.502
much further
than anyone would have expected

1055
00:50:46.586 --> 00:50:48.588
of a bunch of wanna-bes and has-beens.

1056
00:50:48.671 --> 00:50:52.842
If by "has-been" you're referring to me.
I just wanna say I'm flattered.

1057
00:50:52.925 --> 00:50:56.345
because I always considered myself
a never.was.

1058
00:50:56.429 --> 00:50:58.598
Do you mind if I do a quick read on you?

1059
00:50:59.348 --> 00:51:00.349
By all means.

1060
00:51:01.392 --> 00:51:06.022
Okay. I'm picturing a little boy.

1061
00:51:06.105 --> 00:51:09.025
He wants to be a great magician someday.

1062
00:51:09.108 --> 00:51:10.943
And though he's good.
he's not quite good enough.

1063
00:51:11.027 --> 00:51:15.114
So he ends up at the bottom
of the entertainment food chain.

1064
00:51:15.198 --> 00:51:18.785
feeding off of those
who have the talent that he never did.

1065
00:51:18.868 --> 00:51:21.412
Tell me. Am I getting close?

1066
00:51:24.123 --> 00:51:27.084
Wait. Before you go. I'm working
on something new. Do you have a second?

1067
00:51:27.752 --> 00:51:30.588
Okay. Name a card.

1068
00:51:30.671 --> 00:51:32.256
- King of hearts.
- Knew it.

1069
00:51:32.340 --> 00:51:33.549
Okay.

1070
00:51:40.765 --> 00:51:42.225
It's up your left sleeve.

1071
00:51:42.350 --> 00:51:43.851
Is it?

1072
00:51:43.935 --> 00:51:45.686
No. No. I don't see it up there.

1073
00:51:45.770 --> 00:51:49.482
You know. why don't you check
your unnecessary velveteen pocket there?

1074
00:51:51.317 --> 00:51:52.318
Yeah.

1075
00:51:55.822 --> 00:52:00.785
Anyway. thank you so much for coming by.
but this is kind of a talent only area. so...

1076
00:52:02.036 --> 00:52:03.079
Break a leg.

1077
00:52:03.162 --> 00:52:05.206
Hey. you break something. too.

1078
00:52:05.331 --> 00:52:08.459
ANNOUNCER: <i>Ladies and gentlemen.
the Savoy management welcomes you</i>

1079
00:52:08.543 --> 00:52:12.880
<i>to tonight's special performance.
The Four Horse men. Act Two.</i>

1080
00:52:13.089 --> 00:52:15.049
<i>Unlike traditional performances.</i>

1081
00:52:15.258 --> 00:52:18.469
<i>The Four Horse men encourage you to film.
call your friends.</i>

1082
00:52:18.553 --> 00:52:21.514
<i>upload. stream. and tweet the show freely.</i>

1083
00:52:21.722 --> 00:52:25.142
<i>Thank you.
The show will begin in a few minutes.</i>

1084
00:52:29.105 --> 00:52:30.606
Nice watch.

1085
00:52:31.774 --> 00:52:34.110
It's a family heirloom.

1086
00:52:37.280 --> 00:52:39.949
Oh. By the way. I know how he did that trick.

1087
00:52:40.032 --> 00:52:41.868
- Who?
- Shrike.

1088
00:52:41.993 --> 00:52:43.911
So. when he was 14.

1089
00:52:44.036 --> 00:52:46.330
he saw a hole in a tree in Central Park.

1090
00:52:46.539 --> 00:52:49.709
He had a guy who worked at the carousel

1091
00:52:50.001 --> 00:52:52.628
sign a card for what looked
like a routine little trick.

1092
00:52:52.712 --> 00:52:53.880
And?

1093
00:52:54.046 --> 00:52:58.050
At the guy's retirement. 18 years later.

1094
00:52:58.217 --> 00:53:03.264
Shrike performs. has the guy sign a card.
and presto!

1095
00:53:03.514 --> 00:53:04.724
The card is in the tree.

1096
00:53:04.891 --> 00:53:06.767
It was in the tree for 18 years.

1097
00:53:07.018 --> 00:53:08.477
The card was in the tree.

1098
00:53:08.561 --> 00:53:12.565
The tree grew around the card in 18 years.
I mean. that isn't magic. It's not magic.

1099
00:53:12.732 --> 00:53:15.526
The point is. the trick was not to look closely.

1100
00:53:15.735 --> 00:53:20.364
It was to look so far
that you see 20 years into the past.

1101
00:53:20.573 --> 00:53:23.409
After Shrike drowned.
they never found the body.

1102
00:53:23.993 --> 00:53:25.745
What are you suggesting?

1103
00:53:27.747 --> 00:53:28.831
(CROWD CHEERING)

1104
00:53:28.915 --> 00:53:30.917
ANNOUNCER: <i>Arthur Tressler presents</i>

1105
00:53:31.167 --> 00:53:32.418
<i>Jack Wilder.</i>

1106
00:53:32.668 --> 00:53:33.711
<i>Henley Reeves.</i>

1107
00:53:33.920 --> 00:53:35.254
<i>Merritt McKinney.</i>

1108
00:53:35.421 --> 00:53:37.006
<i>and Daniel Atlas.</i>

1109
00:53:37.214 --> 00:53:38.925
<i>The Four Horse men.</i>

1110
00:53:44.096 --> 00:53:45.723
Thank you. Before we begin.

1111
00:53:45.806 --> 00:53:47.850
we'd like to single out
two people in particular.

1112
00:53:47.934 --> 00:53:50.394
A man and a woman to whom
we'd like to dedicate tonight's performance.

1113
00:53:50.478 --> 00:53:52.188
FBI Agent Dylan Rhodes

1114
00:53:52.271 --> 00:53:57.985
and the lovely. if somewhat inexperienced.
Interpol Agent Alma Dray. everyone.

1115
00:53:58.194 --> 00:53:59.195
(CROWD BOOING)

1116
00:53:59.445 --> 00:54:03.199
Yeah. Agent Rhodes
has personally vowed to "nail us."

1117
00:54:03.282 --> 00:54:07.787
And we encourage him to do so
if he has the brains and the fur.

1118
00:54:11.958 --> 00:54:13.751
What is magic?

1119
00:54:13.960 --> 00:54:16.629
Our argument.
nothing but targeted deception.

1120
00:54:18.339 --> 00:54:19.966
So I want you to look.

1121
00:54:20.299 --> 00:54:22.343
Look as closely as possible.

1122
00:54:22.760 --> 00:54:26.722
Because the tricks you are about to see
may not seem connected.

1123
00:54:26.806 --> 00:54:28.724
But we assure you. they are.

1124
00:54:29.684 --> 00:54:32.478
Is what follows 100 different tricks?

1125
00:54:32.812 --> 00:54:36.482
Or is it one giant illusion?

1126
00:54:36.565 --> 00:54:38.317
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

1127
00:54:44.156 --> 00:54:47.326
And now for one
of the oldest tricks in the book.

1128
00:54:47.410 --> 00:54:49.370
Danny. if you wouldn't mind
opening up the box.

1129
00:54:49.453 --> 00:54:51.580
and showing everybody
that it's completely empty.

1130
00:54:51.914 --> 00:54:55.918
Now. we're gonna need
12 courageous volunteers.

1131
00:54:56.127 --> 00:54:58.254
I'm gonna take sweet little Fluffy here.

1132
00:54:58.462 --> 00:55:01.132
and put her inside this mystery box.

1133
00:55:01.716 --> 00:55:04.635
There are two pencils out there.
Hold 'em up high. Let me see 'em.

1134
00:55:04.719 --> 00:55:06.095
- Here!
- WOMAN: Yeah!

1135
00:55:06.762 --> 00:55:08.597
And now. you will say the magic word.

1136
00:55:08.806 --> 00:55:09.932
Abracadabra.

1137
00:55:10.016 --> 00:55:13.060
Yes. and I will wave this magic wand
for no reason. And then...

1138
00:55:13.144 --> 00:55:15.604
Fluffy has magically vanished
before your very eyes.

1139
00:55:17.148 --> 00:55:20.609
If you haven't experienced mass hypnosis.
you're about to.

1140
00:55:20.860 --> 00:55:21.861
And sleep.

1141
00:55:22.028 --> 00:55:24.780
Down. down. Sleep. sleep. Completely sleep.

1142
00:55:24.989 --> 00:55:26.449
Good. good. Sleep. sleep.

1143
00:55:26.657 --> 00:55:30.745
And now we are gonna debunk
a few magic myths this evening.

1144
00:55:30.953 --> 00:55:33.873
We all know that Fluffy is.
in fact. alive and well.

1145
00:55:34.415 --> 00:55:36.834
And Fluffy has miraculously appeared.

1146
00:55:37.043 --> 00:55:38.419
As has the mirror

1147
00:55:38.627 --> 00:55:40.963
which makes the box only
appear as though it's empty.

1148
00:55:41.172 --> 00:55:43.215
When you hear the word "freeze"

1149
00:55:43.424 --> 00:55:45.009
you are all football players.

1150
00:55:45.092 --> 00:55:46.093
(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

1151
00:55:46.177 --> 00:55:48.637
And your job is to tackle.

1152
00:55:48.846 --> 00:55:50.139
dismantle.

1153
00:55:50.347 --> 00:55:51.515
crush.

1154
00:55:51.724 --> 00:55:54.060
tear limb from limb.

1155
00:55:54.435 --> 00:55:56.187
the quarterback.

1156
00:55:57.563 --> 00:56:01.025
Now. we've all heard
of pulling the rabbit out of the hat.

1157
00:56:01.108 --> 00:56:04.111
But has anyone heard
of pulling a hat out of a rabbit?

1158
00:56:08.574 --> 00:56:10.910
You will know who the quarterback is.

1159
00:56:11.077 --> 00:56:14.538
He will be the one saying that word.

1160
00:56:14.747 --> 00:56:15.748
Freeze.

1161
00:56:26.467 --> 00:56:28.385
ALL: Three. two. one...

1162
00:56:35.768 --> 00:56:37.645
Put your hands in the middle.
One. two. three...

1163
00:56:37.728 --> 00:56:39.021
ALL: Kill the quarterback!

1164
00:56:39.313 --> 00:56:40.940
Get on back to your seats.

1165
00:56:41.148 --> 00:56:43.150
I got a feeling I'm gonna be seeing you soon.

1166
00:56:45.778 --> 00:56:46.904
(HENLEY GASPING)

1167
00:56:50.574 --> 00:56:51.742
(AUDIENCE EXCLAIMING IN AWE)

1168
00:57:10.177 --> 00:57:11.178
(HENLEY SCREAMS)

1169
00:57:12.972 --> 00:57:14.056
(LAUGHING)

1170
00:57:15.724 --> 00:57:17.142
I guess you have lost some weight.

1171
00:57:32.783 --> 00:57:34.201
At the intermission.

1172
00:57:34.285 --> 00:57:36.620
we asked you to write down
your current bank balance.

1173
00:57:36.704 --> 00:57:38.205
and seal it in an envelope.

1174
00:57:38.289 --> 00:57:40.749
Now it's time to take those envelopes out.
Everyone take 'em out.

1175
00:57:42.543 --> 00:57:47.089
Now. everybody. shout out your name.
All at once. Go.

1176
00:57:47.298 --> 00:57:48.549
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

1177
00:57:48.799 --> 00:57:49.842
Shout 'em out.

1178
00:57:52.428 --> 00:57:54.346
Clement? Frannick?

1179
00:57:54.555 --> 00:57:56.473
- Yeah! Up here!
- Oh. Way up there.

1180
00:57:56.682 --> 00:57:58.642
Okay. Dina? Robertson?

1181
00:57:58.851 --> 00:57:59.977
That's me!

1182
00:58:00.311 --> 00:58:02.646
Okay. Names. Names. Let's go.

1183
00:58:02.730 --> 00:58:03.814
(SHOUTING CONTINUES)

1184
00:58:04.023 --> 00:58:05.983
Josepha Hickey?

1185
00:58:06.066 --> 00:58:07.109
That's me!

1186
00:58:07.192 --> 00:58:10.112
Josepha. I want you to focus on your balance.

1187
00:58:10.321 --> 00:58:12.281
and count from one to 10 out loud.

1188
00:58:12.489 --> 00:58:14.158
One. two. three. four. five...

1189
00:58:14.241 --> 00:58:15.492
Stop.

1190
00:58:15.618 --> 00:58:16.827
Is the first digit 5?

1191
00:58:17.453 --> 00:58:18.412
Yes.

1192
00:58:18.495 --> 00:58:19.788
Do it again. This time. faster.

1193
00:58:19.914 --> 00:58:21.332
One. two. three. four. five. six...

1194
00:58:21.415 --> 00:58:22.499
Stop.

1195
00:58:23.208 --> 00:58:24.710
Six. Again.

1196
00:58:24.793 --> 00:58:25.794
One. two...

1197
00:58:25.878 --> 00:58:29.840
Josepha. is your
bank balance $562 as of today?

1198
00:58:30.174 --> 00:58:32.343
Yeah. That's what I got.

1199
00:58:32.426 --> 00:58:33.677
(APPLAUSE)

1200
00:58:34.094 --> 00:58:35.638
Unfortunately. you're wrong.

1201
00:58:35.846 --> 00:58:36.889
Okay. Dina.

1202
00:58:38.766 --> 00:58:39.808
1.

1203
00:58:40.392 --> 00:58:41.435
4.

1204
00:58:42.144 --> 00:58:43.145
7.

1205
00:58:44.104 --> 00:58:45.564
- 7.
- Yeah.

1206
00:58:45.648 --> 00:58:49.443
You think it is.
But in fact. you. too. are wrong.

1207
00:58:49.652 --> 00:58:50.694
Uh. Clement...

1208
00:58:50.903 --> 00:58:53.864
You do not have $6.500 in your account.

1209
00:58:54.073 --> 00:58:57.868
In fact. everybody stand up. Everybody.

1210
00:58:59.870 --> 00:59:02.539
Yeah. Put your envelopes to your forehead.

1211
00:59:04.166 --> 00:59:05.626
Focus on your number.

1212
00:59:08.170 --> 00:59:09.380
Ooh! Oh.

1213
00:59:09.880 --> 00:59:12.967
This is... Oh. dear. Just as I feared.

1214
00:59:13.092 --> 00:59:15.260
Oh. this is strange.

1215
00:59:15.678 --> 00:59:18.847
You know. I hate to say this.
but you're all wrong.

1216
00:59:19.056 --> 00:59:20.891
Every last one of you is dead wrong

1217
00:59:20.975 --> 00:59:22.935
about what you think is in your account.

1218
00:59:23.185 --> 00:59:24.937
- Okay. you can sit down now.
- (INAUDIBLE)

1219
00:59:25.312 --> 00:59:27.481
Oh! Oh. yeah. I almost forgot.

1220
00:59:27.564 --> 00:59:30.526
This evening would not be possible

1221
00:59:30.609 --> 00:59:34.697
if it weren't for our great benefactor
Arthur Tressler.

1222
00:59:35.656 --> 00:59:37.282
Big applause! Big applause!

1223
00:59:37.491 --> 00:59:39.952
Art. actually. why don't you come up on stage
for the finale?

1224
00:59:40.160 --> 00:59:41.829
MERRITT: Come on down. Art!
HENLEY: Come on down. Art!

1225
00:59:42.037 --> 00:59:43.831
DANIEL: There he goes. Okay. good.

1226
00:59:44.039 --> 00:59:45.082
Are we on red?

1227
00:59:45.165 --> 00:59:47.084
Bright red. We're all standing by.

1228
00:59:47.292 --> 00:59:48.752
All right. no one leaves the theater. No one.

1229
00:59:48.836 --> 00:59:49.878
DANIEL: There he goes.

1230
00:59:50.629 --> 00:59:52.715
Now. Art. did you fill out your envelope?

1231
00:59:52.923 --> 00:59:54.758
Well. no need. We've done it for you.

1232
00:59:55.426 --> 01:00:00.514
Now. Art. I took a guess.
North of 140. Am I right?

1233
01:00:01.640 --> 01:00:04.309
That's 140 million. by the way.

1234
01:00:07.938 --> 01:00:08.939
I'm sorry. Merritt.

1235
01:00:09.106 --> 01:00:12.109
How can he be right about his balance
and everyone else be wrong?

1236
01:00:12.192 --> 01:00:15.571
I think possibly because he. too. is wrong.

1237
01:00:15.946 --> 01:00:18.157
Everybody. take out your paper.

1238
01:00:18.240 --> 01:00:22.786
And using the flashlight under your seat.
start to warm up that paper.

1239
01:00:22.953 --> 01:00:26.123
I think your correct balance begins to appear.

1240
01:00:29.835 --> 01:00:33.088
Now. Art. don't worry.
we have a flashlight for you.

1241
01:00:33.297 --> 01:00:34.339
Yes.

1242
01:00:35.257 --> 01:00:36.592
(PEOPLE LAUGHING)

1243
01:00:37.843 --> 01:00:38.927
- Whoa!
- (HENLEY LAUGHS)

1244
01:00:41.096 --> 01:00:43.015
DANIEL: Look.
HENLEY: Huh? Wow.

1245
01:00:43.307 --> 01:00:44.516
What's going on there. Daniel?

1246
01:00:44.725 --> 01:00:50.147
Wait. This is weird.
A second ago. it said $144.579.651.

1247
01:00:50.230 --> 01:00:51.231
But now...

1248
01:00:51.857 --> 01:00:54.860
Now it says $70.000 less.

1249
01:00:58.238 --> 01:01:00.574
- Josepha. can you stand up?
- Yes.

1250
01:01:00.657 --> 01:01:02.284
Now. what is your new number?

1251
01:01:02.993 --> 01:01:07.331
$70.562 now in my account.

1252
01:01:07.498 --> 01:01:08.874
(CHEERING)

1253
01:01:10.626 --> 01:01:16.173
Is it possible that Josepha's balance went up
the exact amount that Art's went down?

1254
01:01:16.507 --> 01:01:19.009
Hey. Check it out. It's happening again.

1255
01:01:19.176 --> 01:01:20.219
DANIEL: Is it?

1256
01:01:21.512 --> 01:01:23.847
HENLEY: Wow. It is.

1257
01:01:24.181 --> 01:01:27.351
Art's balance has gone down another 280K.

1258
01:01:27.518 --> 01:01:29.561
Dina Robertson? What did yours say?

1259
01:01:29.812 --> 01:01:33.565
$281.477.

1260
01:01:33.982 --> 01:01:35.234
(CHEERING)

1261
01:01:37.528 --> 01:01:39.196
We have a confession to make.

1262
01:01:39.404 --> 01:01:41.406
She's right. We lied about something.

1263
01:01:41.490 --> 01:01:43.158
Yes. None of you were chosen at random.

1264
01:01:43.283 --> 01:01:45.702
All of you have one thing in common.

1265
01:01:46.245 --> 01:01:48.163
Everyone in this room was a victim

1266
01:01:48.247 --> 01:01:51.041
of the hard times that hit one of
America's most treasured cities.

1267
01:01:51.125 --> 01:01:53.710
Some of you lost your houses. your cars.

1268
01:01:54.211 --> 01:01:56.255
- Your businesses.
- Your loved ones.

1269
01:01:56.380 --> 01:01:59.550
But all of you were insured
by the same company.

1270
01:01:59.716 --> 01:02:01.343
ALL: Tressler Insurance.

1271
01:02:02.886 --> 01:02:03.887
MERRITT: You were abandoned.

1272
01:02:03.971 --> 01:02:05.055
You were loop holed...

1273
01:02:05.139 --> 01:02:06.348
...out of your settlements.

1274
01:02:07.724 --> 01:02:10.352
This is all for show. Correct?

1275
01:02:10.561 --> 01:02:11.812
"All" meaning we're doing it onstage

1276
01:02:11.895 --> 01:02:13.105
in front of a paying audience?

1277
01:02:13.272 --> 01:02:14.898
- Then. yes. it's for show.
- MAN: Whoa! Whoa!

1278
01:02:15.190 --> 01:02:17.693
I've got $82.000 in my bank account!

1279
01:02:17.860 --> 01:02:19.695
It says it right here on my cell phone!

1280
01:02:19.945 --> 01:02:22.906
Everybody. look at your cell phones
right now! Everybody!

1281
01:02:23.073 --> 01:02:24.074
(CELL PHONES CHIMING)

1282
01:02:24.783 --> 01:02:26.201
(ALL CHEERING)

1283
01:02:29.496 --> 01:02:30.581
Whoo!

1284
01:02:30.873 --> 01:02:31.874
Is this for real?

1285
01:02:32.082 --> 01:02:33.250
I don't know.

1286
01:02:33.542 --> 01:02:34.626
DYLAN: <i>Is this happening?</i>

1287
01:02:34.793 --> 01:02:36.378
I don't know! I can't tell!

1288
01:02:37.129 --> 01:02:39.256
Hey! Did you do this?

1289
01:02:40.465 --> 01:02:41.717
JACK:How could we. Art?

1290
01:02:41.925 --> 01:02:43.093
We don't have your password.

1291
01:02:43.260 --> 01:02:46.555
We'd need access to information
we could never get our hands on.

1292
01:02:46.763 --> 01:02:50.475
Ah. yes. security questions. for instance. like.
I don't know. your mother's maiden name

1293
01:02:50.601 --> 01:02:52.144
or the name of your first pet.

1294
01:02:52.269 --> 01:02:54.062
Where would we get that information. Art?

1295
01:02:54.438 --> 01:02:56.064
You certainly would never tell us.

1296
01:02:58.859 --> 01:03:01.069
FULLER: <i>We got confirmation.
It's really happening. They robbed him.</i>

1297
01:03:03.280 --> 01:03:04.740
Do not let them get away.

1298
01:03:04.823 --> 01:03:06.825
Hey. we left you the jet and the Rolls.

1299
01:03:12.080 --> 01:03:13.415
(SHOUTING ANGRILY)

1300
01:03:13.790 --> 01:03:15.125
You got hell to pay!

1301
01:03:18.128 --> 01:03:19.129
DYLAN: Stop!

1302
01:03:19.838 --> 01:03:21.632
Stop! Nobody move!

1303
01:03:23.592 --> 01:03:24.676
Freeze!

1304
01:03:24.927 --> 01:03:26.470
Quarterback!

1305
01:03:29.348 --> 01:03:31.767
ALL: We are The Four Horsemen.

1306
01:03:31.850 --> 01:03:32.893
Good night.

1307
01:03:32.976 --> 01:03:34.102
(GRUNTING)

1308
01:03:45.155 --> 01:03:46.531
DYLAN: Get 'em off me!

1309
01:03:47.282 --> 01:03:48.867
Get off! Get off me!

1310
01:03:56.708 --> 01:03:57.709
(SIRENS WAILING)

1311
01:03:59.253 --> 01:04:00.671
Get off me!

1312
01:04:08.971 --> 01:04:11.139
All right. I want everyone
on the street! Everyone!

1313
01:04:16.270 --> 01:04:17.354
(THADDEUS CHUCKLING)

1314
01:04:18.063 --> 01:04:19.898
ALL: Quarterback!

1315
01:04:21.441 --> 01:04:24.194
Fuller. meet me in front of the theater
and bring the tracker.

1316
01:04:24.736 --> 01:04:27.030
Let's go! Let's go! Now! Come on! Let's go!

1317
01:04:27.197 --> 01:04:28.282
Give me the tracker.

1318
01:04:28.740 --> 01:04:29.741
Let's go.

1319
01:04:33.954 --> 01:04:35.080
FBI! Clear!

1320
01:04:35.789 --> 01:04:36.790
- Dylan!
- DYLAN: Damn.

1321
01:04:37.082 --> 01:04:38.041
What have you got?

1322
01:04:38.125 --> 01:04:39.710
That's him right there. Follow the red dot.

1323
01:04:39.793 --> 01:04:42.838
All right. I'll take this.
Go. Box 'em. Cut 'em off that way.

1324
01:04:44.756 --> 01:04:46.258
He's turning left on Burgundy.

1325
01:05:00.939 --> 01:05:02.399
(CAR ALARMS BLARING)

1326
01:05:08.238 --> 01:05:09.239
(GRUNTS)

1327
01:05:09.906 --> 01:05:11.450
- DYLAN: Oh!
- (CRASHING)

1328
01:05:16.330 --> 01:05:17.789
(TRACKER BEEPING)

1329
01:05:23.337 --> 01:05:24.629
Hey! Move!

1330
01:05:24.963 --> 01:05:26.298
- Move! Move!
- Oh!

1331
01:05:26.590 --> 01:05:28.175
(ALL CLAMORING)

1332
01:05:28.925 --> 01:05:30.469
I got him heading north on Bourbon.

1333
01:05:30.844 --> 01:05:32.554
- Sorry. Move. move!
- Hey!

1334
01:05:32.637 --> 01:05:34.431
Hey. excuse me. Move. move! Excuse me.

1335
01:05:36.141 --> 01:05:37.184
Ow!

1336
01:05:45.901 --> 01:05:47.569
I've lost him at Bourbon.

1337
01:05:52.949 --> 01:05:54.326
Damn! Where are you?

1338
01:06:06.838 --> 01:06:08.048
Excuse me.

1339
01:06:14.346 --> 01:06:15.972
He's heading south on Exchange Place.

1340
01:06:18.517 --> 01:06:19.559
Stop!

1341
01:06:26.566 --> 01:06:27.776
What are you doing?

1342
01:06:31.363 --> 01:06:32.781
DYLAN: He's going in Napoleon House.

1343
01:06:32.864 --> 01:06:33.990
(SIREN WAILS)

1344
01:06:35.617 --> 01:06:37.577
- Move! Move!
- (WOMAN SCREAMS)

1345
01:06:38.036 --> 01:06:39.579
Move out of the way!

1346
01:06:40.247 --> 01:06:41.248
Hey!

1347
01:06:42.082 --> 01:06:43.083
Move!

1348
01:06:45.377 --> 01:06:47.629
He's in the bathroom.
I have him in the bathroom.

1349
01:06:47.754 --> 01:06:50.048
(GRUNTS) No! No! No!

1350
01:06:51.925 --> 01:06:53.093
AGENTS: Freeze!

1351
01:06:53.927 --> 01:06:55.387
- FULLER:Lower your weapons!
- (DEVICES BEEPING)

1352
01:06:55.470 --> 01:06:58.807
What? I'm tracking myself!

1353
01:06:59.307 --> 01:07:01.268
NEWSCASTER: <i>The Horsemen
left egg on the face of what they call</i>

1354
01:07:01.351 --> 01:07:06.648
<i>the alphabet agencies. calling into question
the efficacy of the FBI's task force</i>

1355
01:07:06.898 --> 01:07:09.401
<i>as well as the man in charge
of the investigation.</i>

1356
01:07:09.484 --> 01:07:12.988
<i>Special Agent Dylan Rhodes.
who was publicly ridiculed.</i>

1357
01:07:13.071 --> 01:07:15.949
<i>and even tackled at tonight's performance.</i>

1358
01:07:16.283 --> 01:07:17.576
<i>Talk about a fumble.</i>

1359
01:07:17.784 --> 01:07:19.619
<i>This is quickly becoming a national story.</i>

1360
01:07:19.703 --> 01:07:22.497
<i>as The Horsemen have now seemingly
pulled off the impossible</i>

1361
01:07:22.581 --> 01:07:24.875
<i>for the second time in as many days.</i>

1362
01:07:25.292 --> 01:07:28.462
<i>Two nights ago in Vegas. The Horsemen
seemingly robbed a bank in Paris...</i>

1363
01:07:28.628 --> 01:07:29.796
Hey.

1364
01:07:31.089 --> 01:07:33.633
- What are you doing?
- I'm having a drink.

1365
01:07:36.803 --> 01:07:38.138
I came to get you.

1366
01:07:38.597 --> 01:07:39.598
I'm worried about you.

1367
01:07:39.681 --> 01:07:41.516
You're worried about me.
Well. I'm worried about you.

1368
01:07:41.600 --> 01:07:44.060
- Atlas. You had him.
- He didn't have a weapon.

1369
01:07:44.144 --> 01:07:45.437
I couldn't shoot him and you know that.

1370
01:07:45.520 --> 01:07:48.356
Yeah. but you... You let him go.

1371
01:07:48.773 --> 01:07:49.983
Didn't you?

1372
01:07:50.775 --> 01:07:53.570
A pretty French girl shows up out of the blue.
acts like she's my partner

1373
01:07:53.653 --> 01:07:55.363
- and then she lets the bad guy go?
- Let go of my arm.

1374
01:07:55.447 --> 01:07:57.115
Who exactly are you anyway?

1375
01:07:58.116 --> 01:07:59.201
(GRUNTS)

1376
01:07:59.367 --> 01:08:01.369
I thought you said you were a desk agent.

1377
01:08:06.208 --> 01:08:07.459
Not bad.

1378
01:08:09.461 --> 01:08:10.462
What is this?

1379
01:08:13.507 --> 01:08:14.966
What's the Eye of Horus?

1380
01:08:15.175 --> 01:08:18.261
Oh. certainly nothing
I want to get into tonight.

1381
01:08:18.345 --> 01:08:20.889
You're dismissive enough
about me when you're sober.

1382
01:08:21.181 --> 01:08:23.058
Find your way back yourself.

1383
01:08:27.354 --> 01:08:30.565
Mr. Bradley? Mr. Tressler would like you
to join him for a drink.

1384
01:08:39.950 --> 01:08:40.992
Sir.

1385
01:08:41.201 --> 01:08:42.244
TRESSLER: Thank you.

1386
01:08:43.828 --> 01:08:46.039
What is your role with them?

1387
01:08:46.206 --> 01:08:47.207
Role?

1388
01:08:47.415 --> 01:08:49.125
Yes. You seem to know
everything about them.

1389
01:08:49.209 --> 01:08:51.127
What they're gonna do.
Where they're gonna be.

1390
01:08:51.211 --> 01:08:54.422
If it makes you feel any better.
this wasn't about you.

1391
01:08:54.506 --> 01:08:57.968
Please tell me why this was not about me.

1392
01:08:58.510 --> 01:09:01.096
This is a magic trick. Mr. Tressler.

1393
01:09:01.346 --> 01:09:03.682
Played out on a global scale.

1394
01:09:04.057 --> 01:09:08.019
You. sir. are the abracadabra.

1395
01:09:08.562 --> 01:09:11.356
The distraction.
while they set up the real trick.

1396
01:09:11.565 --> 01:09:15.735
I was a $140-million distraction?

1397
01:09:16.570 --> 01:09:17.737
Yes.

1398
01:09:18.405 --> 01:09:22.576
And that very ego that got you involved
with them in the first place

1399
01:09:23.034 --> 01:09:24.578
is what keeps you from seeing that.

1400
01:09:24.703 --> 01:09:25.996
- You know...
- "I can destroy you."

1401
01:09:26.079 --> 01:09:27.747
Yes. I do know.

1402
01:09:27.956 --> 01:09:29.249
Well. you won't.

1403
01:09:29.791 --> 01:09:31.960
And you won't destroy them.

1404
01:09:32.419 --> 01:09:37.215
Whatever this grand trick is.
it was designed a long time ago.

1405
01:09:37.424 --> 01:09:41.970
And I believe that what's about to follow
is really going to amaze.

1406
01:09:42.804 --> 01:09:47.350
So I suggest you sit back
and enjoy your front row seat.

1407
01:09:47.809 --> 01:09:50.478
You paid quite a lot of good money for it.

1408
01:09:50.687 --> 01:09:52.731
Whatever you stand to make...

1409
01:09:54.858 --> 01:09:58.403
I'll double it. if you expose them now.

1410
01:09:58.612 --> 01:09:59.946
And destroy them.

1411
01:10:00.405 --> 01:10:02.407
I stand to make five million.

1412
01:10:03.116 --> 01:10:04.367
Am I flinching?

1413
01:10:06.494 --> 01:10:08.079
No. you're not.

1414
01:11:28.993 --> 01:11:30.120
Hey.

1415
01:11:31.496 --> 01:11:33.665
I'm sorry for your arm.

1416
01:11:33.748 --> 01:11:35.333
No. I'm sorry.

1417
01:11:35.417 --> 01:11:37.669
I was an asshole. I was drunk.

1418
01:11:39.671 --> 01:11:42.257
I'm at a loss.

1419
01:11:44.175 --> 01:11:49.597
You know. when Merritt said I hardly spent
any time away from the desk. he was right.

1420
01:11:49.681 --> 01:11:52.976
I'm a researcher. That's what I do best.

1421
01:11:54.060 --> 01:11:57.981
So what's this all about?

1422
01:11:58.690 --> 01:12:01.317
Supposedly. if you buy into it.

1423
01:12:01.401 --> 01:12:04.070
The Eye are the keepers of real magic

1424
01:12:04.154 --> 01:12:07.031
and the protectors of those who practice it.

1425
01:12:07.115 --> 01:12:09.075
"Candidates for initiations

1426
01:12:09.159 --> 01:12:12.287
"must follow a series of commands
with blind obedience."

1427
01:12:13.329 --> 01:12:16.541
- This isn't real.
- But there are some who think it is.

1428
01:12:16.958 --> 01:12:18.543
May I?

1429
01:12:20.336 --> 01:12:24.382
According to this.
they only take new people twice a century.

1430
01:12:24.716 --> 01:12:28.136
So what? The Horsemen are doing
these shows in order to get into this thing?

1431
01:12:28.219 --> 01:12:29.429
- I don't know.
- I don't know.

1432
01:12:29.512 --> 01:12:34.517
I mean. I guess these guys
could just rob banks to rob banks.

1433
01:12:34.601 --> 01:12:36.936
They don't have to put on a show for that.

1434
01:12:37.020 --> 01:12:38.521
It's probably just a myth.

1435
01:12:38.605 --> 01:12:42.609
But it doesn't make any sense.
and I don't think logic will solve this for us.

1436
01:12:42.692 --> 01:12:45.278
- You don't say?
- No.

1437
01:12:46.654 --> 01:12:51.284
I believe that some things are only discovered

1438
01:12:51.367 --> 01:12:55.747
if you take certain leaps.

1439
01:13:02.754 --> 01:13:04.255
Well. I gotta get to...

1440
01:13:04.422 --> 01:13:05.882
Yeah. Yeah.

1441
01:13:05.965 --> 01:13:08.134
- Thanks. Good night.
- Yeah. Good night.

1442
01:13:08.218 --> 01:13:10.011
- Sorry.
- It's all right.

1443
01:13:12.514 --> 01:13:14.849
If The Eye did exist. we'd have to assume
they were watching us. right?

1444
01:13:14.933 --> 01:13:15.934
(PHONE BEEPING)

1445
01:13:16.100 --> 01:13:17.310
Shit.

1446
01:13:17.393 --> 01:13:20.021
I think someone is watching us.
but it isn't magic.

1447
01:13:20.104 --> 01:13:23.066
Your fears are correct.
This is not and has never been your phone.

1448
01:13:23.149 --> 01:13:27.862
It's a clone in every way. except for this.

1449
01:13:27.946 --> 01:13:29.239
A bug.

1450
01:13:29.322 --> 01:13:33.159
Someone has heard every call. read every text.

1451
01:13:33.326 --> 01:13:34.577
That's how they were able to stay ahead of us.

1452
01:13:34.661 --> 01:13:35.453
God damn it!

1453
01:13:36.955 --> 01:13:38.706
Get me Atlas' interrogation tape.

1454
01:13:38.957 --> 01:13:41.209
Yes. sir. I have it on the hard drive.

1455
01:13:42.335 --> 01:13:43.419
Picture's up.

1456
01:13:43.878 --> 01:13:45.630
DYLAN: Okay. fast forward.

1457
01:13:46.005 --> 01:13:47.465
Go on. go on. Freeze!

1458
01:13:48.258 --> 01:13:50.051
Okay. Frame by frame. Go on.

1459
01:13:50.927 --> 01:13:51.970
Play it through.

1460
01:13:53.096 --> 01:13:55.390
Ah! Stop. Zoom in tighter. Tighter.

1461
01:13:55.848 --> 01:13:57.642
There. That's where he took my phone.

1462
01:13:58.935 --> 01:14:00.228
Is that thing transmitting?

1463
01:14:00.311 --> 01:14:01.729
Only when you're making a call
or sending a text.

1464
01:14:01.896 --> 01:14:02.855
Plus I removed the bug.

1465
01:14:02.939 --> 01:14:04.482
All right. Put it back in and turn on the phone.

1466
01:14:04.732 --> 01:14:06.526
They don't know that we know about the bug.

1467
01:14:06.734 --> 01:14:08.736
As of this instant. we are ahead of them.

1468
01:14:08.820 --> 01:14:10.905
We need to keep it that way. Understand?

1469
01:14:11.364 --> 01:14:12.657
Find my real phone and track it.

1470
01:14:12.740 --> 01:14:15.785
Already did. As of about 20 minutes ago.
it's in New York City.

1471
01:14:16.327 --> 01:14:17.370
Good.

1472
01:14:17.745 --> 01:14:20.540
I wanna cut 'em off at the knees.
They got power? Cut it.

1473
01:14:20.832 --> 01:14:24.127
They got phones. electricity. water? Cut it.

1474
01:14:24.335 --> 01:14:27.088
Squeeze 'em out.
I want 'em to feel our presence.

1475
01:14:27.297 --> 01:14:28.756
And get me an airplane!

1476
01:14:31.551 --> 01:14:32.635
The firewall's down.

1477
01:14:32.719 --> 01:14:34.178
- Do they know about this?
- DANIEL: They who?

1478
01:14:34.262 --> 01:14:36.180
"They." "them." whoever we're working for.

1479
01:14:36.264 --> 01:14:39.892
Who are we working for?
And are we prepared to go to jail for them?

1480
01:14:39.976 --> 01:14:42.186
- DANIEL: Stop being paranoid.
- It really does happen.

1481
01:14:42.270 --> 01:14:44.105
It happened to you.
Doesn't mean it's gonna happen to us.

1482
01:14:44.188 --> 01:14:45.773
Guys. I don't know if can do this. all right.

1483
01:14:45.857 --> 01:14:47.150
I don't want to go to jail. you know?

1484
01:14:47.233 --> 01:14:49.027
Then don't screw up.
You're always talking about wanting

1485
01:14:49.110 --> 01:14:50.111
to be treated like an adult.

1486
01:14:50.194 --> 01:14:51.571
Now might be a good time
to start acting like one.

1487
01:14:51.654 --> 01:14:53.781
Stick to the plan. Stay here and burn it all.

1488
01:14:56.993 --> 01:14:58.244
(TIRES SCREECHING)

1489
01:15:06.919 --> 01:15:08.046
MERRITT:I don't know what I'm doing here.

1490
01:15:08.129 --> 01:15:09.213
I don't know what you would do
anywhere else.

1491
01:15:09.297 --> 01:15:12.091
I'm here for the pot of gold
at the end of the rainbow.

1492
01:15:12.175 --> 01:15:14.218
That's it. Then I'm gone.

1493
01:15:14.302 --> 01:15:16.679
You can do whatever you want
when this is over. Merritt.

1494
01:15:16.763 --> 01:15:18.723
But until then. you stick to the plan.

1495
01:15:18.806 --> 01:15:20.933
Hey. guys. Uh... They're here.

1496
01:15:22.852 --> 01:15:24.729
- My guys are ready to go.
- Let's do this quickly...

1497
01:15:24.937 --> 01:15:26.147
- Uh. No.
- What?

1498
01:15:26.230 --> 01:15:27.690
She doesn't have jurisdiction here.

1499
01:15:27.774 --> 01:15:28.983
She's Interpol. She's with me.

1500
01:15:29.067 --> 01:15:31.277
- She stays.
- What? What?

1501
01:15:31.569 --> 01:15:32.570
Stay in the car.

1502
01:15:34.822 --> 01:15:36.032
Let's go.

1503
01:15:41.829 --> 01:15:42.872
MERRITT: Okay. Let's do it.

1504
01:15:47.168 --> 01:15:48.169
FBI!

1505
01:15:52.423 --> 01:15:53.758
MERRITT: Ladies first.

1506
01:15:54.342 --> 01:15:55.635
- Don't move!
- (SCREAMING)

1507
01:16:01.140 --> 01:16:03.059
- (CELL PHONE RINGING)
- Tell me.

1508
01:16:03.142 --> 01:16:04.727
Is my money being well-spent?

1509
01:16:05.395 --> 01:16:07.271
- Exceedingly well.
- (CAMERA CLICKING)

1510
01:16:09.065 --> 01:16:10.566
Now you tell me.

1511
01:16:11.359 --> 01:16:12.694
how do you like your Horsemen?

1512
01:16:12.777 --> 01:16:15.154
Fricasseed or fried?

1513
01:16:15.238 --> 01:16:16.280
Shredded.

1514
01:16:17.615 --> 01:16:19.075
I'll tell the chef.

1515
01:17:24.682 --> 01:17:26.058
(GRUNTING)

1516
01:17:28.853 --> 01:17:30.188
(DISPOSAL WHIRRING)

1517
01:17:34.650 --> 01:17:35.651
Freeze!

1518
01:17:42.867 --> 01:17:43.993
- Dylan!
- (WHIRRING)

1519
01:17:44.786 --> 01:17:45.953
DYLAN: Hold on!

1520
01:17:48.289 --> 01:17:49.332
Oh. you little...

1521
01:17:53.836 --> 01:17:54.837
Come here!

1522
01:17:56.589 --> 01:17:58.508
OFFICER: Five is clear. Standing by for six.

1523
01:17:58.841 --> 01:18:00.718
- You little shit!
- (IMITATING) You little shit!

1524
01:18:00.968 --> 01:18:03.095
- What game are you playing?
- What game are you playing?

1525
01:18:03.596 --> 01:18:05.515
We're all good at six. Move to seven.

1526
01:18:05.598 --> 01:18:07.642
Copy that. Going to seven. Go. go. go!

1527
01:18:08.559 --> 01:18:10.228
No. no. no. no. no. Go back!

1528
01:18:11.103 --> 01:18:12.230
Hey!

1529
01:18:13.981 --> 01:18:15.233
DYLAN: Come here!

1530
01:18:18.611 --> 01:18:19.779
(GRUNTING)

1531
01:18:22.448 --> 01:18:23.658
Ah!

1532
01:18:46.264 --> 01:18:47.390
Come here!

1533
01:18:47.473 --> 01:18:49.183
All right. whoa. hold on. hold on!

1534
01:18:51.102 --> 01:18:52.937
- Really?
- Yup.

1535
01:18:53.437 --> 01:18:54.438
Ow!

1536
01:18:57.108 --> 01:18:58.109
Oh. you...

1537
01:18:59.485 --> 01:19:00.486
Ow!

1538
01:19:01.529 --> 01:19:02.989
You little... (YELLING)

1539
01:19:09.203 --> 01:19:10.204
(GRUNTS)

1540
01:19:19.422 --> 01:19:20.464
Shit!

1541
01:19:27.179 --> 01:19:28.306
(DYLAN YELLING)

1542
01:19:38.858 --> 01:19:39.901
Shit!

1543
01:19:39.984 --> 01:19:41.152
(PANTING)

1544
01:19:41.319 --> 01:19:42.320
Give me that!

1545
01:19:42.570 --> 01:19:43.613
(GROANS)

1546
01:20:06.385 --> 01:20:07.637
(CAR LOCK CHIRPS)

1547
01:20:08.554 --> 01:20:10.139
FULLER: <i>All units. covert he north exit now!</i>

1548
01:20:10.222 --> 01:20:11.307
Clear on Evan.

1549
01:20:11.849 --> 01:20:13.392
FULLER: <i>Block every possible exit.</i>

1550
01:20:13.517 --> 01:20:14.644
Hey! Get back... Shit.

1551
01:20:16.395 --> 01:20:18.522
- FBI. Sort of. I need your car. Thanks.
- What?

1552
01:20:18.606 --> 01:20:19.607
What?

1553
01:20:22.234 --> 01:20:23.861
Stop! Stop!

1554
01:20:32.203 --> 01:20:33.287
(GRUNTS)

1555
01:20:40.002 --> 01:20:41.045
Hey!

1556
01:20:43.381 --> 01:20:45.800
- (GROANING)
- (HANDCUFFS CLICKING)

1557
01:21:10.825 --> 01:21:11.826
Good. Follow him!

1558
01:21:11.909 --> 01:21:13.994
Don't ever tell me to stay in the car. Ever.

1559
01:21:14.078 --> 01:21:15.413
I didn't have tactical command.

1560
01:21:15.496 --> 01:21:17.832
If you don't trust me. just tell me.

1561
01:21:17.915 --> 01:21:19.500
Promise me. next time. you will back me up.

1562
01:21:19.583 --> 01:21:21.669
Could we have
this conversation later. please?

1563
01:21:21.752 --> 01:21:23.337
No!

1564
01:21:23.421 --> 01:21:25.631
Okay. fine. I promise. Now. go!

1565
01:21:27.925 --> 01:21:29.343
(TIRES SQUEALING)

1566
01:21:33.055 --> 01:21:35.599
- Whoa! Where'd they go?
- Where are they?

1567
01:21:35.850 --> 01:21:37.518
I don't know. She just took some guy's car.

1568
01:21:37.601 --> 01:21:39.061
- Where are they?
- That way. That way.

1569
01:21:39.145 --> 01:21:40.187
- Is that your car?
- Yeah.

1570
01:21:40.271 --> 01:21:41.731
Let's go.

1571
01:21:55.828 --> 01:21:56.954
(GRUNTS)

1572
01:21:57.121 --> 01:21:58.122
- (BRAKES SQUEAL)
- Whoa!

1573
01:22:07.256 --> 01:22:08.299
There he is!

1574
01:22:17.767 --> 01:22:19.310
(SIRENS WAILING)

1575
01:22:20.102 --> 01:22:21.103
DYLAN: Move!

1576
01:22:25.483 --> 01:22:26.525
Left!

1577
01:22:28.819 --> 01:22:30.362
We're heading east on the FDR Drive.

1578
01:22:30.571 --> 01:22:32.490
- This is not east.
- North! North!

1579
01:22:32.573 --> 01:22:34.617
- We're heading north on the FDR Drive.
- What?

1580
01:22:34.700 --> 01:22:36.786
MALE NEWSCASTER: <i>We're coming
to you live above the FDR.</i>

1581
01:22:36.869 --> 01:22:39.789
<i>where NYPD and federal agents.
as you now see.</i>

1582
01:22:39.872 --> 01:22:43.209
<i>are engaged in a high-speed pursuit.
following a black sedan.</i>

1583
01:22:48.339 --> 01:22:49.340
DYLAN: <i>Fuller. where are you?</i>

1584
01:22:49.840 --> 01:22:51.509
Right here. Trying to catch up to you now.

1585
01:22:51.675 --> 01:22:53.719
NEWSCASTER: <i>We're now trying
to get you a better shot.</i>

1586
01:22:56.222 --> 01:22:57.348
Come on!

1587
01:23:04.605 --> 01:23:05.648
Whoa!

1588
01:23:05.731 --> 01:23:06.732
Sorry.

1589
01:23:09.902 --> 01:23:10.903
Whoa!

1590
01:23:12.947 --> 01:23:16.158
NEWSCASTER: <i>It looks like they're turning
onto the 59th Street Bridge.</i>

1591
01:23:18.327 --> 01:23:22.331
<i>As soon as we have them within range.
we will bring you those pictures live.</i>

1592
01:23:27.378 --> 01:23:28.546
Good. Just stay with him.

1593
01:23:31.298 --> 01:23:32.633
(SIRENS WAILING)

1594
01:23:35.928 --> 01:23:37.179
Go. go. go!

1595
01:23:38.013 --> 01:23:39.056
(YELLS)

1596
01:23:41.225 --> 01:23:42.726
Behind... You're behind the bus!

1597
01:23:46.313 --> 01:23:47.398
Get over!

1598
01:23:48.148 --> 01:23:49.233
Ha-ha!

1599
01:23:50.943 --> 01:23:51.986
Oh. shit!

1600
01:23:54.446 --> 01:23:55.489
Uh-oh!

1601
01:24:15.551 --> 01:24:16.552
Come here!

1602
01:24:17.845 --> 01:24:19.263
Get back! Get back!

1603
01:24:20.723 --> 01:24:22.057
Dylan. let's go. man!

1604
01:24:22.224 --> 01:24:23.267
Come on. you...

1605
01:24:24.727 --> 01:24:26.812
FULLER: Come on. man! Get out!
DYLAN: He's gonna die in here.

1606
01:24:26.896 --> 01:24:30.232
Leave him! There's nothing you can do!
Let's go! Leave him!

1607
01:24:35.070 --> 01:24:36.447
- DYLAN: The paper!
- FULLER: Dylan!

1608
01:24:36.697 --> 01:24:38.616
Let's go! Let's go! Come on!

1609
01:25:03.932 --> 01:25:05.976
NEWSCASTER: <i>Today.
the unfolding story of a popular</i>

1610
01:25:06.143 --> 01:25:08.187
<i>and controversial group of magicians.</i>

1611
01:25:08.270 --> 01:25:10.272
<i>who have been fast capturing
the public's imagination.</i>

1612
01:25:10.356 --> 01:25:13.692
<i>took a dark turn
when a police action that began in Chinatown</i>

1613
01:25:13.776 --> 01:25:17.571
<i>developed into a dramatic. high-speed chase
across the 59th Street Bridge.</i>

1614
01:25:17.655 --> 01:25:20.616
<i>which caused a fatal collision
that took the life of Jack Wilder.</i>

1615
01:25:20.699 --> 01:25:22.993
<i>one of the so-called Four Horse men.</i>

1616
01:25:24.203 --> 01:25:28.290
<i>The whereabouts of the other three
Horsemen remain unknown at this time.</i>

1617
01:25:33.170 --> 01:25:35.714
FULLER: Dylan. they just
figured out what the paper was in Jack's car.

1618
01:25:35.839 --> 01:25:37.007
So they know what it is?

1619
01:25:37.216 --> 01:25:38.842
And why the kid died trying to protect it.

1620
01:25:39.009 --> 01:25:40.552
Evans is on his way to brief us right now.

1621
01:25:40.761 --> 01:25:41.804
Let's go.

1622
01:25:42.388 --> 01:25:43.722
You're gonna wanna take this first. though.

1623
01:25:43.806 --> 01:25:44.765
What's that?

1624
01:25:44.848 --> 01:25:46.558
Your friend Thaddeus Bradley.

1625
01:25:47.685 --> 01:25:48.686
Rhodes.

1626
01:25:49.019 --> 01:25:50.604
You do understand the function

1627
01:25:50.688 --> 01:25:52.856
of the magician's assistant.
don't you. Agent Rhodes?

1628
01:25:53.190 --> 01:25:55.859
Yeah. she's there to distract them
while he sets up the trick.

1629
01:25:56.276 --> 01:25:59.279
(CHUCKLES) You'd be right
if you weren't so wrong.

1630
01:25:59.697 --> 01:26:01.407
<i>While you're watching the magician.</i>

1631
01:26:02.074 --> 01:26:04.660
<i>that lovely innocent is actually
pulling the strings.</i>

1632
01:26:04.743 --> 01:26:07.830
<i>Don't you find it peculiar that Interpol
would send you</i>

1633
01:26:07.913 --> 01:26:11.417
a first timer off the desk to be your assistant?

1634
01:26:11.917 --> 01:26:14.086
Why did she request to be put on the case?

1635
01:26:14.420 --> 01:26:16.380
- She was assigned to the case.
- <i>Oh.</i>

1636
01:26:17.381 --> 01:26:18.757
Luck of the draw.

1637
01:26:19.216 --> 01:26:22.261
Like choosing a random card in the deck.

1638
01:26:22.469 --> 01:26:26.014
I find it odd. your sudden act of generosity.

1639
01:26:26.098 --> 01:26:27.266
What's in it for you?

1640
01:26:27.433 --> 01:26:29.268
Just trying to even the game.

1641
01:26:29.560 --> 01:26:33.397
I feel like I'm playing with somebody
wearing ankle weights and flippers.

1642
01:26:34.606 --> 01:26:38.402
Keep up. Agent Rhodes. Keep up.

1643
01:26:42.239 --> 01:26:43.282
FULLER: Hey.

1644
01:26:43.615 --> 01:26:44.825
We got a problem.

1645
01:26:45.993 --> 01:26:47.077
COWAN: Here's the safe.

1646
01:26:47.161 --> 01:26:49.955
No. no. no. Hey. What's he doing here?

1647
01:26:50.122 --> 01:26:51.582
Giving us our first solid lead.

1648
01:26:51.665 --> 01:26:54.752
We've been investigating a private security
contractor called Elkhorn

1649
01:26:54.835 --> 01:26:56.503
- for the last five years.
- And?

1650
01:26:56.587 --> 01:26:58.714
They've been hiding close
to a half billion dollars...

1651
01:26:58.797 --> 01:27:01.300
I didn't ask you. I asked him.

1652
01:27:01.675 --> 01:27:03.886
The money's in a vault inside
a warehouse in Queens.

1653
01:27:03.969 --> 01:27:06.472
We think this vault
is your magicians' final target.

1654
01:27:06.847 --> 01:27:08.557
COWAN: The magician
who died on the bridge...

1655
01:27:08.640 --> 01:27:12.269
You pulled our classified Elkhorn file
right from his crispy little hand.

1656
01:27:12.561 --> 01:27:14.897
And despite their bullshit
Robin Hood razzle-dazzle.

1657
01:27:14.980 --> 01:27:16.732
your magicians are nothing
more than common thieves.

1658
01:27:16.815 --> 01:27:17.983
How did they get the file?

1659
01:27:19.443 --> 01:27:22.446
This is the part you're gonna find
particularly interesting. Agent Rhodes.

1660
01:27:22.654 --> 01:27:27.367
They patched to my server after they accessed
your mobile command center in New Orleans

1661
01:27:27.451 --> 01:27:29.036
with codes they got from your phone.

1662
01:27:31.163 --> 01:27:32.998
You ordered us all out to chase after them.

1663
01:27:33.457 --> 01:27:35.918
The level of incompetence
displayed on this case.

1664
01:27:36.001 --> 01:27:38.003
that's a magic trick in and of itself.

1665
01:27:38.670 --> 01:27:40.964
Abracadabra. I'm taking over.

1666
01:27:42.382 --> 01:27:44.301
Boss. he's taking over?

1667
01:27:44.843 --> 01:27:46.345
EVANS: Let's go. gentlemen.

1668
01:27:48.180 --> 01:27:49.181
DYLAN: Hey.

1669
01:27:49.306 --> 01:27:51.183
Hey. I want to have a word with you.

1670
01:27:51.266 --> 01:27:52.392
Don't ever talk to me like that again.

1671
01:27:52.476 --> 01:27:54.853
- Why the hell did you take this case?
- What?

1672
01:27:54.937 --> 01:27:57.022
People say I'm "hard to read."
That's an American expression.

1673
01:27:57.105 --> 01:27:58.357
Do you understand it?

1674
01:27:58.482 --> 01:27:59.525
Yes.

1675
01:27:59.650 --> 01:28:01.652
Good. then let me make myself
perfectly clear to you.

1676
01:28:01.860 --> 01:28:05.656
If I find out that you are anything other than
who you say you are. I swear...

1677
01:28:05.781 --> 01:28:07.491
And we French also have an expression.

1678
01:28:08.158 --> 01:28:09.284
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

1679
01:28:09.368 --> 01:28:10.953
"Faith can move mountains."

1680
01:28:11.161 --> 01:28:14.790
If we hope to capture The Horsemen.
then you need to have a little faith in me.

1681
01:28:14.998 --> 01:28:17.000
Because I've done nothing
to deserve otherwise.

1682
01:28:17.167 --> 01:28:19.795
I just got my ass handed to me.

1683
01:28:19.878 --> 01:28:21.421
I am losing this case.

1684
01:28:21.505 --> 01:28:24.842
So faith is a luxury
I don't have any time for right now.

1685
01:28:31.056 --> 01:28:33.267
DANIEL: <i>More than anything in his life.</i>

1686
01:28:33.350 --> 01:28:38.772
Jack wanted to be
the most famous magician who ever lived.

1687
01:28:38.856 --> 01:28:40.232
And I can't say he achieved it.

1688
01:28:40.315 --> 01:28:44.236
but I do hope wherever he is.
it is full of magic.

1689
01:28:46.029 --> 01:28:48.365
But the point is... Sorry.

1690
01:28:48.448 --> 01:28:49.908
The point is...

1691
01:28:49.992 --> 01:28:56.206
The point of why we are here is to say
that we are not... We cannot quit now.

1692
01:28:56.290 --> 01:28:58.792
<i>We've started something bigger than all of us.</i>

1693
01:28:58.876 --> 01:29:00.711
<i>We have to finish it.</i>

1694
01:29:03.255 --> 01:29:04.923
(SIRENS WAILING)

1695
01:29:09.803 --> 01:29:10.888
MAN: <i>Approaching the warehouse.</i>

1696
01:29:11.054 --> 01:29:13.599
<i>Units 5 and 6
covert he north and south entrances.</i>

1697
01:29:13.849 --> 01:29:15.100
<i>We are going for the vault.</i>

1698
01:29:19.938 --> 01:29:22.858
Hey. Where's the safe? Where's the safe?

1699
01:29:27.070 --> 01:29:28.030
EVANS: What is this?

1700
01:29:28.113 --> 01:29:29.406
Where the hell is the goddamn safe?

1701
01:29:29.573 --> 01:29:31.366
We just moved it while you were outside.

1702
01:29:31.533 --> 01:29:32.701
- Evans' orders.
- COWAN: What?

1703
01:29:32.784 --> 01:29:33.827
I never said that.

1704
01:29:33.911 --> 01:29:36.872
Sir. you got a phone call
and said Washington wants the safe moved.

1705
01:29:37.080 --> 01:29:39.124
You never heard that
come out of my mouth. Agent.

1706
01:29:39.249 --> 01:29:39.750
What happened?

1707
01:29:39.917 --> 01:29:42.294
What happened? You tell me what's going on.
because this is bullshit!

1708
01:29:42.377 --> 01:29:43.754
No!

1709
01:29:45.672 --> 01:29:47.299
(CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING)

1710
01:29:49.635 --> 01:29:51.136
Jesus Christ.

1711
01:29:51.303 --> 01:29:54.306
Sir? Sir? What are you doing?

1712
01:29:54.389 --> 01:29:56.224
I think it's Beethoven's <i>Concerto in D-Major.</i>

1713
01:29:56.308 --> 01:29:58.477
- Where's the safe?
- His team is loading the truck.

1714
01:30:02.814 --> 01:30:04.483
- Hey! Hey!
- Hey!

1715
01:30:06.026 --> 01:30:07.194
- DYLAN: Stop the truck!
- Stop!

1716
01:30:08.195 --> 01:30:09.613
- Stop!
- Hey! Stop that truck!

1717
01:30:10.322 --> 01:30:12.366
(DYLAN AND FULLER CONTINUE YELLING)

1718
01:30:18.997 --> 01:30:20.874
What the hell's going on? We got our orders.

1719
01:30:20.958 --> 01:30:22.459
Now you've got new orders. Open it up.

1720
01:30:26.672 --> 01:30:28.131
Okay. Here's what I want.

1721
01:30:28.507 --> 01:30:30.801
At this moment.
they think that safe's leaving this site.

1722
01:30:31.176 --> 01:30:34.304
So we stay with it.
We follow it all the way to... Where's it going?

1723
01:30:34.388 --> 01:30:35.639
5 Pointz. Up the street.

1724
01:30:35.973 --> 01:30:38.850
So we go to 5 Pointz.
Wherever the safe goes. we go.

1725
01:30:39.017 --> 01:30:40.143
It'll lead us right to 'em.

1726
01:30:41.019 --> 01:30:42.229
You two are with me.

1727
01:30:54.992 --> 01:30:55.993
Guys...

1728
01:30:57.077 --> 01:30:59.496
Look. Office just called with this.

1729
01:30:59.579 --> 01:31:01.623
Horsemen posted it to YouTube
20 minutes ago.

1730
01:31:01.707 --> 01:31:05.669
<i>The point of why we're here
is to say that we are not...</i>

1731
01:31:05.752 --> 01:31:07.546
<i>We cannot quit now.</i>

1732
01:31:07.754 --> 01:31:11.717
<i>We've started something bigger than all of us.
We have to finish it.</i>

1733
01:31:11.800 --> 01:31:14.636
<i>Remember the name Jack Wilder
when you see us live.</i>

1734
01:31:14.720 --> 01:31:16.513
<i>5 Pointz. Queens. 7:</i><i>00.</i>

1735
01:31:16.596 --> 01:31:19.141
Their show is in a half an hour.
It's exactly where we're headed.

1736
01:31:19.224 --> 01:31:21.643
I don't know. boss.
I don't wanna be the naysayer.

1737
01:31:21.727 --> 01:31:23.645
but these guys are kinda tricky.

1738
01:31:23.729 --> 01:31:26.356
Rhodes. they're entertainers.

1739
01:31:28.942 --> 01:31:31.111
NEWSCASTER 1 : <i>A stunning
turnout here in 5 Pointz</i>

1740
01:31:31.194 --> 01:31:34.489
<i>as the renegade Horsemen
taunt the FBI into a final showdown.</i>

1741
01:31:34.573 --> 01:31:36.491
NEWSCASTER 2: <i>The Horsemen have
invited us to their final round</i>

1742
01:31:36.575 --> 01:31:38.744
<i>of their three-act face-off with the FBI.</i>

1743
01:31:39.244 --> 01:31:42.622
<i>What do they have in store?
We're about to find out.</i>

1744
01:31:42.748 --> 01:31:44.541
(CROWD CHEERING)

1745
01:31:45.292 --> 01:31:46.793
(SIRENS WAILING)

1746
01:31:53.967 --> 01:31:56.178
COWAN: <i>All eyes on the truck.
Let's see who approaches.</i>

1747
01:31:56.261 --> 01:31:57.262
Copy that.

1748
01:32:13.820 --> 01:32:15.614
FEMALE FBI AGENT: <i>Agents Rhodes. Fuller?</i>

1749
01:32:16.323 --> 01:32:17.324
Go. for us.

1750
01:32:17.449 --> 01:32:19.951
We've got movement.
Someone's walking toward the truck.

1751
01:32:20.160 --> 01:32:21.286
<i>It's a woman.</i>

1752
01:32:25.457 --> 01:32:26.833
- FULLER: Freeze!
- Oh. shit!

1753
01:32:26.917 --> 01:32:28.126
(GUNS COCKING)

1754
01:32:28.418 --> 01:32:29.920
THADDEUS: What the hell's going on?

1755
01:32:30.962 --> 01:32:33.298
COWAN: Hey! It's the guy from the TV.

1756
01:32:33.381 --> 01:32:34.424
Put your guns down.

1757
01:32:34.674 --> 01:32:37.385
Look who it is. The fifth Horseman.

1758
01:32:37.469 --> 01:32:40.680
Are you kidding?
I'm following them. just like you are.

1759
01:32:40.764 --> 01:32:43.934
I'm not following anybody anymore.
You've been ahead of us this whole time.

1760
01:32:44.017 --> 01:32:45.644
But guess what? I'm ahead of you now.

1761
01:32:45.977 --> 01:32:47.646
Your ass is mine.

1762
01:32:47.813 --> 01:32:49.481
You guys are still idiots.

1763
01:32:49.564 --> 01:32:51.817
- Yeah?
- This happens to be the former

1764
01:32:51.900 --> 01:32:53.985
rehearsal space for Lionel Shrike.

1765
01:32:54.653 --> 01:32:56.488
It's where I did my first show.

1766
01:32:56.655 --> 01:32:59.491
Now. if you wanna look
like even bigger idiots.

1767
01:32:59.658 --> 01:33:00.951
why not open it?

1768
01:33:01.326 --> 01:33:02.953
And while you're doing it. Agent Rhodes.

1769
01:33:03.370 --> 01:33:07.040
would you mind reenacting your look
of absolute befuddlement for me?

1770
01:33:07.290 --> 01:33:09.376
It will make a wonderful cover for my DVD.

1771
01:33:10.836 --> 01:33:11.837
Open the safe.

1772
01:33:11.920 --> 01:33:12.963
- Go ahead.
- DYLAN: Open it.

1773
01:33:16.967 --> 01:33:18.677
- (BEEPS)
- AGENT: What the hell?

1774
01:33:21.221 --> 01:33:22.305
What?

1775
01:33:22.556 --> 01:33:26.017
Give me that. No. No!

1776
01:33:29.312 --> 01:33:30.564
(LOCK TUMBLERS MOVING)

1777
01:33:30.689 --> 01:33:31.731
What is this?

1778
01:33:32.023 --> 01:33:33.733
- (CLUNKING)
- Get back!

1779
01:33:39.489 --> 01:33:40.866
(BALLOONS SQUEAKING)

1780
01:33:41.283 --> 01:33:43.410
Who doesn't love a good magic trick?

1781
01:33:44.202 --> 01:33:46.538
They have you chasing empty safes again.

1782
01:33:47.873 --> 01:33:51.084
Once again. misdirection.

1783
01:33:58.049 --> 01:33:59.551
The show is starting. Move out!

1784
01:33:59.759 --> 01:34:02.220
The question I'd be asking now.
Agent Rhodes is...

1785
01:34:02.721 --> 01:34:04.890
"What happened to the real one?"

1786
01:34:21.740 --> 01:34:22.949
(SIRENS BLARING)

1787
01:34:25.535 --> 01:34:27.287
COWAN: Clear! Clear 'em out!

1788
01:34:27.370 --> 01:34:28.914
Come on. Move 'em out.
Move 'em out of the way.

1789
01:34:30.373 --> 01:34:32.250
FBI! Give me a path!

1790
01:34:32.876 --> 01:34:34.461
Clear out! Clear out!

1791
01:34:34.711 --> 01:34:36.087
DANIEL: <i>What is magic?</i>

1792
01:34:36.922 --> 01:34:37.964
<i>Magic is deception.</i>

1793
01:34:38.089 --> 01:34:41.593
<i>But deception designed to delight.
to entertain. to inspire.</i>

1794
01:34:41.676 --> 01:34:44.137
Look out! Clear! Clear! Look out!

1795
01:34:44.596 --> 01:34:45.722
DANIEL: <i>It is about belief</i>

1796
01:34:45.805 --> 01:34:46.806
MERRITT: <i>Faith.</i>

1797
01:34:46.932 --> 01:34:47.891
HENLEY: <i>Trust.</i>

1798
01:34:47.974 --> 01:34:49.100
(CROWD CHEERING)

1799
01:34:51.937 --> 01:34:53.271
<i>Without those qualities.</i>

1800
01:34:53.396 --> 01:34:56.816
<i>magic. as an art form. would no longer exist.</i>

1801
01:34:57.400 --> 01:35:01.529
HENLEY: <i>But what happens if these qualities
are not used for their higher purpose?</i>

1802
01:35:01.613 --> 01:35:04.282
<i>And instead they're used to cheat. lie.</i>

1803
01:35:04.366 --> 01:35:06.576
DANIEL: <i>For personal gain or for greed.</i>

1804
01:35:06.993 --> 01:35:08.745
<i>Then it's no longer magic.</i>

1805
01:35:08.828 --> 01:35:09.913
<i>It's crime.</i>

1806
01:35:10.121 --> 01:35:16.253
<i>So tonight. for our final act.
you're gonna help us set a few things right.</i>

1807
01:35:20.173 --> 01:35:21.341
What's going on here. Rhodes?

1808
01:35:21.591 --> 01:35:22.759
I don't know.

1809
01:35:23.802 --> 01:35:25.011
Showtime.

1810
01:35:30.141 --> 01:35:31.184
Look!

1811
01:35:35.480 --> 01:35:37.399
There they are on the roof. Let's move!

1812
01:35:37.482 --> 01:35:38.817
Go. go. go!

1813
01:35:39.526 --> 01:35:40.819
- Dylan!
- FBI. coming through!

1814
01:35:42.279 --> 01:35:43.238
What are you doing here?

1815
01:35:43.321 --> 01:35:45.865
They're going in the wrong direction
and you know it.

1816
01:35:46.199 --> 01:35:48.410
Rhodes! I need all personnel now!

1817
01:35:48.493 --> 01:35:51.830
You need to trust me. Take your leap of faith.

1818
01:35:52.789 --> 01:35:53.832
Wait.

1819
01:35:54.290 --> 01:35:55.417
I'm going to go with her.

1820
01:35:55.625 --> 01:35:56.835
Go. I got your back. I'll be right here.

1821
01:35:58.503 --> 01:35:59.379
Go ahead!

1822
01:35:59.546 --> 01:36:01.006
That's on you. Fuller.

1823
01:36:16.646 --> 01:36:20.650
Let's go. let's go! Now. now. now!

1824
01:36:31.828 --> 01:36:32.871
Daniel?

1825
01:36:33.621 --> 01:36:34.831
- Yeah?
- Uh...

1826
01:36:34.956 --> 01:36:39.419
As our. let's call it. year of living dangerously

1827
01:36:39.502 --> 01:36:43.048
comes to a close.
in a rare moment of vulnerability.

1828
01:36:43.131 --> 01:36:47.844
I'd like to express a sentiment
to you about our relationship.

1829
01:36:47.927 --> 01:36:48.970
Okay.

1830
01:36:49.304 --> 01:36:52.807
Well. when I first met you.
I thought you were kind of a

1831
01:36:54.642 --> 01:36:56.561
- dick.
- (LAUGHS) Oh.

1832
01:36:56.644 --> 01:36:58.021
(LAUGHS) And?

1833
01:37:00.023 --> 01:37:01.691
No. that's it.

1834
01:37:01.941 --> 01:37:02.901
That's very nice.

1835
01:37:02.984 --> 01:37:04.402
- Yeah.
- I'm touched.

1836
01:37:04.486 --> 01:37:06.071
Yeah. Just from the heart.

1837
01:37:06.321 --> 01:37:07.822
Well. I didn't tell you where I was touched.

1838
01:37:07.906 --> 01:37:08.948
Oh. you!

1839
01:37:09.032 --> 01:37:10.200
(CHUCKLING)

1840
01:37:12.660 --> 01:37:14.329
Oh. God.
What are we gonna do when this is over?

1841
01:37:14.621 --> 01:37:17.457
We're on our own.
Our instructions run out after the show.

1842
01:37:18.333 --> 01:37:21.795
Even if there is no "Eye."
if we were completely played and we spend

1843
01:37:21.878 --> 01:37:26.382
the next 20 years in jail. then.
I just want to say that...

1844
01:37:26.633 --> 01:37:29.010
I know. Me. too.

1845
01:37:29.344 --> 01:37:32.305
Whoa. (LAUGHS)
Little too sentimental for me.

1846
01:37:37.143 --> 01:37:38.645
(CHEERING)

1847
01:37:39.229 --> 01:37:40.313
There they are!

1848
01:37:43.316 --> 01:37:46.027
Go grab 'em! Put 'em down! Go. go. go!

1849
01:37:46.194 --> 01:37:47.195
Grab 'em!

1850
01:37:48.696 --> 01:37:49.739
(CROWD GROANS)

1851
01:37:51.032 --> 01:37:52.075
(CROWD LAUGHING)

1852
01:37:52.200 --> 01:37:53.243
Get up!

1853
01:37:53.701 --> 01:37:54.869
What the hell?

1854
01:37:58.665 --> 01:37:59.833
Ah. shit!

1855
01:38:00.917 --> 01:38:02.418
(PANTING)

1856
01:38:09.050 --> 01:38:10.552
- HENLEY: Hello. New York!
- (CROWD CHEERING)

1857
01:38:18.768 --> 01:38:20.645
Thank you for the magic.

1858
01:38:20.895 --> 01:38:25.108
And thank you for being such
an incredible and dedicated audience.

1859
01:38:25.525 --> 01:38:29.404
Unfortunately. like all good things.
it must come to an end.

1860
01:38:32.115 --> 01:38:34.284
So we would like to start our show tonight...

1861
01:38:34.701 --> 01:38:36.244
By saying goodbye.

1862
01:38:36.411 --> 01:38:37.495
(CHEERING)

1863
01:38:37.579 --> 01:38:40.790
HENLEY:All we wanted was to
bring the world to a magic show.

1864
01:38:40.874 --> 01:38:43.418
DANIEL: And thereby bring a little magic
back to the world.

1865
01:38:47.797 --> 01:38:48.923
DYLAN: Clear the way!

1866
01:38:58.725 --> 01:39:01.936
MERRITT: This has been
one hell of a ride for all of us.

1867
01:39:02.437 --> 01:39:04.772
But it's time for us to disappear.

1868
01:39:04.981 --> 01:39:06.316
DANIEL: Good night. New York.

1869
01:39:06.566 --> 01:39:07.942
MERRITT: And thank you for believing in us.

1870
01:39:10.612 --> 01:39:11.779
DYLAN: Stop!

1871
01:39:15.283 --> 01:39:16.284
Freeze!

1872
01:39:17.118 --> 01:39:18.328
- No!
- (GUNSHOT)

1873
01:39:35.970 --> 01:39:37.263
God damn it!

1874
01:40:05.875 --> 01:40:07.085
I'm sorry.

1875
01:40:07.710 --> 01:40:09.837
You were right. It's bigger than all of us.

1876
01:40:10.838 --> 01:40:14.926
This is one time I'm not happy being right.

1877
01:40:17.220 --> 01:40:18.972
So I guess this is it.

1878
01:40:20.890 --> 01:40:22.058
Is it?

1879
01:40:48.042 --> 01:40:49.335
Dylan!

1880
01:40:49.752 --> 01:40:52.005
Dylan! Dylan!

1881
01:40:52.297 --> 01:40:53.339
Hey.

1882
01:40:54.757 --> 01:40:56.676
- You see that?
- What?

1883
01:41:00.346 --> 01:41:01.723
Where's the real money?

1884
01:41:08.313 --> 01:41:09.439
(CAR ALARM BLARING)

1885
01:41:17.947 --> 01:41:21.909
MAN: You're under arrest!
Hands in the air! Now!

1886
01:42:13.044 --> 01:42:14.170
I've been framed.

1887
01:42:15.505 --> 01:42:18.049
- I'm sure you were.
- Yeah. but I can prove it.

1888
01:42:18.383 --> 01:42:19.675
I always do.

1889
01:42:20.051 --> 01:42:22.011
Just like I predicted that you'd play the fool.

1890
01:42:22.095 --> 01:42:24.597
Let's just drop the theatricality. all right?

1891
01:42:24.847 --> 01:42:27.016
The cameras aren't rolling in here.

1892
01:42:27.225 --> 01:42:29.685
Fellas. can I have a few minutes
with my friend here alone. please.

1893
01:42:29.769 --> 01:42:30.895
GUARD: Sure.

1894
01:42:36.609 --> 01:42:37.652
THADDEUS: All right.

1895
01:42:38.694 --> 01:42:40.321
- I got information to trade.
- Mmm.

1896
01:42:40.405 --> 01:42:41.531
I believe that's how it's done. Huh?

1897
01:42:41.614 --> 01:42:43.241
If it's of some value.

1898
01:42:45.910 --> 01:42:49.080
These bars give a man time to think.

1899
01:42:50.248 --> 01:42:53.543
And I'm pretty sure I know how they did it.

1900
01:42:54.210 --> 01:42:56.295
<i>Remember the rabbit trick
in the second show?</i>

1901
01:42:57.255 --> 01:42:59.090
<i>The box was never empty.</i>

1902
01:43:00.174 --> 01:43:01.342
(WHIRRING)

1903
01:43:01.467 --> 01:43:02.635
<i>The room wasn't either.</i>

1904
01:43:04.053 --> 01:43:06.431
<i>After gaining access to the warehouse.</i>

1905
01:43:06.639 --> 01:43:08.724
<i>The Horsemen left the real safe</i>

1906
01:43:08.808 --> 01:43:13.771
<i>and transformed the whole room
into a giant rabbit box.</i>

1907
01:43:15.398 --> 01:43:20.236
<i>You go charging in there.
thinking the safe was already gone.</i>

1908
01:43:20.445 --> 01:43:21.446
Hey!

1909
01:43:21.529 --> 01:43:22.822
Hey! Stop!

1910
01:43:23.030 --> 01:43:24.282
Missing the trick. Again.

1911
01:43:24.365 --> 01:43:27.535
Which was to make you think
the safe had already been stolen.

1912
01:43:27.618 --> 01:43:29.704
so you'd drop your guard and leave.

1913
01:43:30.246 --> 01:43:33.207
<i>Now. while you were busy
playing with balloon animals.</i>

1914
01:43:33.416 --> 01:43:36.002
<i>someone was breaking into the warehouse.</i>

1915
01:43:54.520 --> 01:43:55.688
<i>Who?</i>

1916
01:43:57.106 --> 01:43:58.608
<i>Jack Wilder.</i>

1917
01:43:59.358 --> 01:44:00.693
Holy shit.

1918
01:44:00.902 --> 01:44:03.279
No. No way. He died right in front of my eyes.

1919
01:44:04.071 --> 01:44:06.157
Unless. of course. he didn't.

1920
01:44:13.498 --> 01:44:14.790
It's locked.

1921
01:44:15.583 --> 01:44:16.792
JACK: Weren't you listening?

1922
01:44:17.293 --> 01:44:18.336
Nothing's ever locked.

1923
01:44:18.503 --> 01:44:19.587
MERRITT: Ah!

1924
01:44:19.754 --> 01:44:22.340
Well done. Mr. Wilder! Good work.

1925
01:44:22.423 --> 01:44:24.383
MERRITT: You're a big boy now. Jack.

1926
01:44:24.467 --> 01:44:26.844
He escaped in a standard FBI vehicle. right?

1927
01:44:30.890 --> 01:44:32.225
<i>Led you to the bridge.</i>

1928
01:44:32.475 --> 01:44:36.103
<i>Where the other Horse men were waiting
with an identical replacement car.</i>

1929
01:44:37.104 --> 01:44:39.190
<i>It only took a split second
for you to lose contact with it</i>

1930
01:44:39.273 --> 01:44:40.274
<i>and make the switch.</i>

1931
01:44:50.201 --> 01:44:51.285
(MERRITT LAUGHS)

1932
01:44:53.538 --> 01:44:54.956
- Oh!
- (LAUGHS)

1933
01:45:02.588 --> 01:45:05.591
THADDEUS: <i>When you crawled
into that burning car.</i>

1934
01:45:05.967 --> 01:45:07.969
<i>quite heroically. I might add.</i>

1935
01:45:09.845 --> 01:45:11.931
<i>you almost died trying to rescue</i>

1936
01:45:12.014 --> 01:45:15.017
<i>what I assume was a cadaver
from the morgue.</i>

1937
01:45:16.519 --> 01:45:20.189
DYLAN: <i>Why go through such an elaborate
and dangerous plan</i>

1938
01:45:21.065 --> 01:45:23.276
- just to frame one guy?
- I don't know.

1939
01:45:23.359 --> 01:45:25.361
They never kept any of the money they took.

1940
01:45:25.444 --> 01:45:27.822
Yeah. that's the part
I haven't been able to put together yet.

1941
01:45:27.905 --> 01:45:30.491
But I just gave you information that
is substantially more important.

1942
01:45:30.575 --> 01:45:32.451
- No. Not really.
- What?

1943
01:45:32.535 --> 01:45:36.872
I finally got a chance to really look into
Lionel Shrike.

1944
01:45:37.290 --> 01:45:40.126
His comeback attempt. His accident.

1945
01:45:41.085 --> 01:45:44.589
The insurer who denied the family's claim?

1946
01:45:44.839 --> 01:45:46.048
Tressler Insurance.

1947
01:45:47.967 --> 01:45:50.219
The bank that carried the note?

1948
01:45:51.262 --> 01:45:52.847
Credit Republican of Paris.

1949
01:45:52.930 --> 01:45:54.515
Credit Republicain de Paris.

1950
01:45:56.142 --> 01:45:57.435
DYLAN: What do you make of that?

1951
01:45:57.643 --> 01:45:59.604
A sucker is born every minute.

1952
01:46:00.563 --> 01:46:05.818
What if all this was just leading up to us
getting mugged in Central Park at 2:00 a.m.?

1953
01:46:05.901 --> 01:46:08.070
No. I'm telling you.
we're right where we need to be.

1954
01:46:08.821 --> 01:46:11.073
- We just have to find...
- That?

1955
01:46:13.618 --> 01:46:15.369
DANIEL: The Lionel Shrike tree.

1956
01:46:16.120 --> 01:46:18.122
HENLEY: And the card encased in glass.

1957
01:46:20.166 --> 01:46:21.626
What do we do now?

1958
01:46:38.434 --> 01:46:39.894
Oh. nice!

1959
01:46:41.687 --> 01:46:43.856
(CAROUSEL MUSIC PLAYING)

1960
01:46:55.868 --> 01:46:57.328
DYLAN: <i>So. here's my new theory.</i>

1961
01:46:57.662 --> 01:47:01.123
The legend is that the "Eye" is everywhere.

1962
01:47:01.791 --> 01:47:02.958
Waiting

1963
01:47:03.334 --> 01:47:07.129
for the truly great magicians
to distinguish themselves

1964
01:47:08.089 --> 01:47:09.840
from the mediocre ones.

1965
01:47:10.591 --> 01:47:11.842
Maybe that was you.

1966
01:47:12.551 --> 01:47:14.804
Deep down inside you wanted nothing more

1967
01:47:14.887 --> 01:47:17.264
than to be part of the "Eye."
but you were never invited.

1968
01:47:17.598 --> 01:47:20.685
So you try to destroy them.
But instead what happens?

1969
01:47:21.227 --> 01:47:22.687
You pissed them off.

1970
01:47:24.438 --> 01:47:27.441
The Eye isn't real.

1971
01:47:27.525 --> 01:47:30.611
Okay. then. explain then.
Who's behind all this.

1972
01:47:31.070 --> 01:47:32.655
Somebody with an obsession.

1973
01:47:32.738 --> 01:47:33.906
- Meticulous.
- Who?

1974
01:47:33.989 --> 01:47:37.159
Somebody prepared to sacrifice everything.

1975
01:47:37.243 --> 01:47:41.455
Somebody so prepared to lose
that they wouldn't even be a suspect

1976
01:47:41.539 --> 01:47:42.581
until the trick was done.

1977
01:47:42.665 --> 01:47:45.376
I don't want a profile. I need a name.
Who? Who?

1978
01:47:45.459 --> 01:47:47.169
I don't know who.

1979
01:47:47.628 --> 01:47:51.132
But they had to have access to the warehouse
to plant the mirrors.

1980
01:47:52.550 --> 01:47:56.470
Always a step ahead of me. And the FBI.

1981
01:47:56.554 --> 01:47:59.807
Got past them not once.
not twice. but consistently.

1982
01:48:00.224 --> 01:48:02.226
Almost as if they were on the in...

1983
01:48:15.614 --> 01:48:16.824
DYLAN: (WHISPERING) The inside.

1984
01:48:29.128 --> 01:48:31.505
- You.
- Mmm.

1985
01:48:34.759 --> 01:48:35.926
Why?

1986
01:48:36.594 --> 01:48:38.721
That is the question. isn't it?

1987
01:48:39.764 --> 01:48:40.848
You're right.

1988
01:48:41.932 --> 01:48:46.353
I can't tell you how long I've waited
to see the look on your face.

1989
01:48:48.814 --> 01:48:50.149
Who are you?

1990
01:48:51.400 --> 01:48:52.777
What do you want from me?

1991
01:48:53.652 --> 01:48:55.154
What do I want?

1992
01:48:55.571 --> 01:48:58.491
I want you to spend
the rest of your life in this cell.

1993
01:48:58.574 --> 01:49:02.578
staring at four walls
and wondering how you missed it.

1994
01:49:03.287 --> 01:49:06.373
How you let yourself
be so blinded by your ego

1995
01:49:06.916 --> 01:49:09.335
that you convinced yourself
that you were one step ahead

1996
01:49:09.418 --> 01:49:11.754
when you were always two steps behind.

1997
01:49:16.801 --> 01:49:17.927
Dylan?

1998
01:49:19.011 --> 01:49:20.012
Wait a minute.

1999
01:49:21.055 --> 01:49:22.973
Dylan! How did this happen?

2000
01:49:25.768 --> 01:49:26.769
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

2001
01:49:28.479 --> 01:49:29.688
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

2002
01:49:30.856 --> 01:49:32.525
Dylan!

2003
01:49:32.691 --> 01:49:33.692
Why?

2004
01:49:34.151 --> 01:49:35.152
Why?

2005
01:49:39.448 --> 01:49:41.534
- MERRITT: Oh. my God.
- (JACK CHUCKLING)

2006
01:49:42.576 --> 01:49:45.746
I did not see that coming. That's impossible!

2007
01:49:45.830 --> 01:49:46.872
JACK: No way.

2008
01:49:46.956 --> 01:49:49.375
That was actually pretty good.

2009
01:49:49.792 --> 01:49:50.835
Thank you.

2010
01:49:51.293 --> 01:49:53.587
When I said.
"Always be the smartest guy in the room."

2011
01:49:53.671 --> 01:49:54.630
We were in agreement.

2012
01:49:54.713 --> 01:49:55.756
Okay. Right.

2013
01:49:56.423 --> 01:49:57.424
Henley.

2014
01:49:58.175 --> 01:49:59.885
I've never seen her speechless.

2015
01:50:00.010 --> 01:50:01.720
I take that as a huge compliment.

2016
01:50:02.429 --> 01:50:05.099
Hey. man. I'm so sorry for kicking your ass.
Really.

2017
01:50:05.933 --> 01:50:11.146
Hey. listen. for the record.
I have always been a 100% believer.

2018
01:50:11.230 --> 01:50:14.483
And the amount of energy I have expended
to keep these infidels on point...

2019
01:50:14.567 --> 01:50:15.693
(HENLEY LAUGHING)

2020
01:50:15.776 --> 01:50:17.820
Merritt. you're in.

2021
01:50:18.654 --> 01:50:19.697
God bless.

2022
01:50:19.822 --> 01:50:20.865
DYLAN: Come.

2023
01:50:21.907 --> 01:50:26.996
The real magic is taking four strong solo acts
and making them all work together.

2024
01:50:27.079 --> 01:50:29.248
And that's exactly what you did.

2025
01:50:30.666 --> 01:50:31.709
So welcome.

2026
01:50:35.045 --> 01:50:37.131
Welcome to the Eye.

2027
01:50:39.425 --> 01:50:40.551
(HENLEY GASPS)

2028
01:51:44.281 --> 01:51:45.783
It was all connected.

2029
01:51:47.034 --> 01:51:50.037
Credit Republican. Tressler Insurance.

2030
01:51:52.206 --> 01:51:53.332
<i>Bonjour.</i>

2031
01:51:55.042 --> 01:51:56.293
<i>Bonjour.</i>

2032
01:51:59.421 --> 01:52:02.758
And Elkhorn?
What's the connection to Shrike?

2033
01:52:05.344 --> 01:52:10.891
Elkhorn started as a safe manufacturer.
They used cheap steel.

2034
01:52:12.476 --> 01:52:13.519
They cut corners.

2035
01:52:13.852 --> 01:52:16.981
When he got to the bottom of the river.
the safe warped.

2036
01:52:17.064 --> 01:52:18.440
And he was trapped.

2037
01:52:20.067 --> 01:52:21.694
He was your father.

2038
01:52:23.612 --> 01:52:26.949
DYLAN: <i>The morning before the show
didn't feel like any other day.</i>

2039
01:52:27.991 --> 01:52:32.996
<i>When my fathers aid he had to go to work.
he could see that I didn't want him to leave.</i>

2040
01:52:35.290 --> 01:52:40.421
<i>So he gave me his watch. and he told me
to count the seconds until he came back.</i>

2041
01:52:41.588 --> 01:52:44.258
<i>I have never let his watch stop since then.</i>

2042
01:52:44.341 --> 01:52:46.468
And from that moment on.

2043
01:52:46.552 --> 01:52:49.138
I created a persona.

2044
01:52:49.763 --> 01:52:51.640
I planned. I worked out every detail.

2045
01:52:51.724 --> 01:52:55.018
But the one thing
that I couldn't imagine happening

2046
01:52:55.477 --> 01:52:56.645
was you.

2047
01:52:58.313 --> 01:53:01.275
And I know that the logical conclusion for you

2048
01:53:01.775 --> 01:53:04.486
is to take this case to its resolution.

2049
01:53:04.570 --> 01:53:07.656
And for you to turn me in.

2050
01:53:12.745 --> 01:53:13.829
Yeah.

2051
01:53:15.789 --> 01:53:19.626
But you know how I feel
about resolution and logic.

2052
01:53:21.003 --> 01:53:22.337
And you also know

2053
01:53:23.172 --> 01:53:27.509
that I think some things
are best left unexplained.

2054
01:53:34.016 --> 01:53:35.726
DYLAN: One more secret to lock away.

2055
01:53:36.435 --> 01:53:37.895
(ALMA CHUCKLES)

2056
01:53:40.481 --> 01:53:42.024
- Hmm.
- (LAUGHS)

2057
01:54:03.295 --> 01:54:04.546
DYLAN: <i>Come in close.</i>

2058
01:54:05.297 --> 01:54:06.465
<i>Closer.</i>

2059
01:54:06.799 --> 01:54:08.759
DANIEL: <i>Because now you know our secret.</i>

2060
01:54:09.009 --> 01:54:11.386
MERRITT: <i>We could be anywhere.
Watching you.</i>

2061
01:54:11.929 --> 01:54:14.807
HENLEY: <i>We're looking for someone
to help us with our next trick.</i>

2062
01:54:15.641 --> 01:54:18.185
JACK: <i>On the count of three. open your eyes</i>

2063
01:54:18.268 --> 01:54:19.895
<i>and tell me what you see.</i>

2064
01:54:21.230 --> 01:54:22.314
DYLAN: <i>One.</i>

2065
01:54:22.439 --> 01:54:23.482
<i>Two...</i>

2066
01:55:55.365 --> 01:55:57.242
DANIEL: Please. stop. stop. stop.

2067
01:55:57.659 --> 01:56:01.330
All right. stop the van. Stop the van.
I'm gonna jump out of the van.

2068
01:56:02.331 --> 01:56:03.832
Oh. thank God.

2069
01:56:05.751 --> 01:56:07.836
HENLEY: Where are we?

2070
01:56:07.919 --> 01:56:10.339
Great. another shit hole.

2071
01:56:10.422 --> 01:56:12.382
Okay. feeling it.

2072
01:56:12.466 --> 01:56:16.637
I'm exhausted. and hungry. and cranky.

2073
01:56:17.679 --> 01:56:19.514
HENLEY: Check out this place.

2074
01:56:19.598 --> 01:56:20.932
MERRITT: Where'd you bring us?

2075
01:56:21.058 --> 01:56:22.434
DANIEL:Was there no landfill where we were?

2076
01:56:22.517 --> 01:56:24.353
JACK: This place is awesome.

2077
01:56:25.896 --> 01:56:27.606
- Is this our new gear?
- DANIEL: There'd better not be. like.

2078
01:56:27.689 --> 01:56:29.650
matching jumpsuits in there.
You know I don't wear spandex.

2079
01:56:29.733 --> 01:56:30.859
It's locked.

2080
01:56:31.026 --> 01:56:32.110
Guys. the cards.

2081
01:56:32.194 --> 01:56:33.403
What card?

2082
01:56:33.528 --> 01:56:34.738
DANIEL: What do you mean. "what card"?

2083
01:56:36.823 --> 01:56:37.824
Hmm.

2084
01:56:38.867 --> 01:56:39.868
Okay.

2085
01:56:40.160 --> 01:56:41.995
(UPBEAT SONG PLAYING)

2086
02:00:31.850 --> 02:00:33.602
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

2086
